spect it.', 67736, 0), (428470, 'I''ve always seen the Olympics as a place where you could act out your differences on the athletic field with a sense of sportsmanship and fairness and mutual respect.', 28632, 0), (428471, 'When people do not respect us we are sharply offended yet in his private heart no man much respects himself. ', 286, 0), (428472, 'Let them hate me, provided they respect my conduct.', 67737, 0), (428473, 'Each state, so that it does not abridge the great fundamental rights belonging, under the Constitution, to all citizens, may grant or withhold such civil rights as it pleases; all that is required is that, in this respect, its laws shall be impartial.', 67738, 0), (428474, 'All of my Polynesian counterparts in the NFL with roots in American Samoa understand how the values embedded in our South Pacific culture - community, hard work, perseverance, respect - contribute directly to our success.', 67739, 0), (428475, 'We are at a point now where people respect us and respect our work - the guys want to sit down and watch women''s matches.', 67740, 0), (428476, 'There is respect for law, and then there is complicity in lawlessness.', 17503, 0), (428477, 'We, as Turkey, call on Europe to respect human rights and democracy.', 67741, 0), (428478, 'Against my will, in the course of my travels, the belief that everything worth knowing was known at Cambridge gradually wore off. In this respect my travels were very useful to me.', 95, 0), (428479, 'I don''t want to be bored I don''t want to be with someone I don''t respect. ', 18322, 0), (428480, 'What''s natural and right is to go with the energy of how it all has to work together. What''s natural and right is interconnectedness, not individualism. What is natural and right is respect for the system, not killing the system. What''s natural and right is love.', 65236, 0), (428481, 'Show respect to all people, but grovel to none.', 35521, 0), (428482, 'And Barack and I were raised with so many of the same values, like you work hard for what you want in life. That your word is your bond; that you do what you say you''re going to do. That you treat people with dignity and respect, even if you don''t know them and even if you don''t agree with them.', 1997, 0), (428483, 'We owe our law enforcement officers the highest respect.', 67742, 0), (428484, 'I grew up with just my mum and sister, so I respect women a lot.', 500, 0), (428485, 'If man doesn''t learn to treat the oceans and the rain forest with respect, man will become extinct.', 13539, 0), (428486, 'There may be fairies at the bottom of the garden. There is no evidence for it, but you can''t prove that there aren''t any, so shouldn''t we be agnostic with respect to fairies?', 1716, 0), (428487, 'To the living we owe respect, but to the dead we owe only the truth.', 808, 0), (428488, 'Not just Christians and Jews, but also Muslims, Buddhists, Hindus and the followers of many other religions believe in values like peace, respect, tolerance and dignity. These are values that bring people together and enable us to build responsible and solid communities.', 67743, 0), (428489, 'The highest ideals are human intelligence, creativity and love. Respect these above all.', 9137, 0), (428490, 'A brainy person does not abuse copyright instead they respect it and uphold it. ', 67593, 0), (428491, 'The new republic should be based on diversity, respect and equal rights for all.', 67744, 0), (428492, 'We players are as normal human beings as anyone else, and we also have the right to live a normal life. I don''t understand why people talk so much about the way we dress up, how we walk, what we eat, and every little detail of ours. Players are the real heroes. Sports have both respect and fame, and I am fortunate enough to be a sportsperson.', 66912, 0), (428493, 'All respect for the office of the presidency aside, I assumed that the obvious and unadulterated decline of freedom and constitutional sovereignty, not to mention the efforts to curb the power of judicial review, spoke for itself.', 28287, 0), (428494, 'We''ve got to work to save our children and do it with full respect for the fact that if we do not, no one else is going to do it.', 64252, 0), (428495, 'We are a people of many different religions and many different faiths. The only way forward in a pluralistic society of diverse faiths such as ours is to have laws that protect and respect the freedom of all, equally.', 67011, 0), (428496, 'I get no respect. The way my luck is running, if I was a politician I would be honest.', 2242, 0), (428497, 'All I ever seek from good deeds is a measure of respect.', 67745, 0), (428498, 'To get down to the quick of it, respect motivates me - not success.', 43985, 0), (428499, 'I believe no matter who you are, respect yourself, respect others.', 67746, 0), (428500, 'Respect for the rights of others means peace.', 17480, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (428501, 'Those who wish to pet and baby wild animals ''love'' them. But those who respect their natures and wish to let them live normal lives, love them more.', 12943, 0), (428502, 'I cleaned up my act, and I made this rap thing work for me. I thought people would respect me for that. But instead, it''s, ''Oh, he''s sold all these records, and now he thinks he''s all that.''', 67747, 0), (428503, 'Dance is a universal language, and whether you know how to dance or grew up training in dance, you have a respect for people who love to dance, and it''s also visually very entertaining to watch a great dancer.', 67748, 0), (428504, 'I respect anyone who has to fight and howl for his decency.', 30909, 0), (428505, 'I think people have different definitions of team unity. My definition is doing whatever it takes to win, what makes a great team; it''s performance on the field, respect on the field.', 29415, 0), (428506, 'Each and every one of us is amazing in our own way. We have five beautiful women who exude talent, and I am blessed and honored to be one of those women. For me, the bottom line is it''s all about respect and love, and I have both for Fifth Harmony.', 67749, 0), (428507, 'Nothing is more destructive of respect for the government and the law of the land than passing laws which cannot be enforced.', 104, 0), (428508, 'Discretion is nothing other than the sense of justice with respect to the sphere of the intimate contents of life.', 23121, 0), (428509, 'I think it is very important for any U.S. administration to be clear that America stands on the side of freedom and democracy and respect for individual rights.', 67750, 0), (428510, 'Each minute is a little thing, and yet, with respect to our personal productivity, to manage the minute is the secret of success.', 4294, 0), (428511, 'The first lesson my kids got about the ocean was to respect it. You can never turn your back on the ocean when you''re dealing with tides and currents - factors beyond your control. You have to be the CEO of your family on the water. CEO stands for ''constant eyes on,'' and it''s something I never forget.', 67751, 0), (428512, 'That you may retain your self-respect, it is better to displease the people by doing what you know is right, than to temporarily please them by doing what you know is wrong.', 62367, 0), (428513, 'We must not permit our respect for the dead or our sympathy for the living to lead us into an act of injustice to the balance of the living.', 65656, 0), (428514, 'I do respect people''s faith, but I don''t respect their manipulation of that faith in order to create fear and control.', 4141, 0), (428515, 'Labor wants pride and joy in doing good work, a sense of making or doing something beautiful or useful - to be treated with dignity and respect as brother and sister.', 52621, 0), (428516, 'I try to be kind to people, to treat them with respect. And I''m proud of that.', 67752, 0), (428517, 'A lot of the powerful religious leaders, from Jesus to Buddha to Tibetan monks, they''re really talking about the same things: love and acceptable, and the value of friendship, and respecting yourself so you can respect others.', 67753, 0), (428518, 'I have great respect for my parents. I got such beautiful things from both of them. It doesn''t mean that we didn''t have our rough times, but they were remarkable people who were open-minded, creative and hard-working, and had great senses of humor.', 1883, 0), (428519, 'If we were all determined to play the first violin we should never have an ensemble. therefore, respect every musician in his proper place.', 19830, 0), (428520, 'The mandate I have received and for which I will speak with heart and head to implement over the next seven years had its four pillars - an inclusive citizenship, equality and participation and respect in a creative society creating an excellence in everything we Irish do.', 67754, 0), (428521, 'Most of those coming from the mainland are very destitute, almost naked. I am trying to find places for those able to work, and provide for them as best I can, so as to lighten the burden on the Government as much as possible, while at the same time they learn to respect themselves by earning their own living.', 1799, 0), (428522, 'I''ve never done online dating, but first of all, I have a book out called ''Make It Last Forever: The Do''s and The Dont''s,'' which led me to do the online dating thing. A lot of people respect my relationship songs, so they can pretty much trust me.', 67755, 0), (428523, 'When you are learning about a martial art, it is about respect.', 67756, 0), (428524, 'You must respect people and work hard to be in shape. And I used to train very hard. When the others players went to the beach after training, I was there kicking the ball.', 12296, 0), (428525, 'I''ve got no respect for any young man who won''t join the colors.', 15993, 0), (428526, 'I''ve got tremendous respect for different cultures, for the food and everything.', 67757, 0), (428527, 'I''m always pushing for human responsibility. Given that chimpanzees and many other animals are sentient and sapient, then we should treat them with respect.', 2086, 0), (428528, 'Go up close to your friend, but do not go over to him! We should also respect the enemy in our friend.', 11, 0), (428529, 'Respect is not ever assigned it''s earned. ', 67758, 0), (428530, 'I believe mutual respect for one another and cooperation should be the basis for relationships with foreign nations.', 40212, 0), (428531, 'Respect for the truth comes close to being the basis for all morality.', 1265, 0), (428532, 'What I respect as far as in myself and in others is the spirit of just doing it. For better or worse, it may work and it may not, but I''m going to go for it. Ultimately I probably prefer to be respected for that than whether it works out or not, either winning or losing.', 43985, 0), (428533, 'It''s all about respect. I''m not going to treat a woman like a piece of meat.', 67759, 0), (428534, 'Civilization is built on a number of ultimate principles... respect for human life, the punishment of crimes against property and persons, the equality of all good citizens before the law... or, in a word justice.', 67760, 0), (428535, 'The sanctity of our battlefields, monuments, and veterans institutions is of utmost importance to preserve military history and pay respect to those who fought.', 67761, 0), (428536, 'I look for these qualities and characteristics in people. Honesty is number one, respect, and absolutely the third would have to be loyalty.', 67247, 0), (428537, 'I have a new found respect for women who have been through breast cancer and this surgery.', 58431, 0), (428538, 'I couldn''t do country, with all due respect to all country music artists. My parents dressed me up with a cowboy hat and we''d go to the rodeo when I was younger and it traumatized me for life.', 1738, 0), (428539, 'I certainly respect other people''s opinions, but I would not vote for a woman to be the pastor of a church.', 67762, 0), (428540, 'Steve Irwin did wonderful conservation work but I was uncomfortable about some of his stunts. Even if animals aren''t aware that you are not treating them with respect, the viewers are.', 3969, 0), (428541, 'I have always admired and had enormous respect for Elizabeth Taylor. She was not only an incredible actress but an amazing woman as well.', 67763, 0), (428542, 'People are roasting each other at parties, at work events, around the fire. It''s so fun. People are busting each other''s chops, and it''s a sign of affection, truly. It''s a true test of love and friendship: can you make a man laugh at himself? So what makes a good burn? Go after targets you love and respect. And hit ''em hard.', 67151, 0), (428543, 'Worrying about how you''ll be remembered is pointless. Better to try to live your life in such a way that people will respect you while you''re still alive.', 67764, 0), (428544, 'Perhaps I seek certain utopian things, space for human honour and respect, landscapes not yet offended, planets that do not exist yet, dreamed landscapes.', 2043, 0), (428545, 'Journalism should be more like science. As far as possible, facts should be verifiable. If journalists want long-term credibility for their profession, they have to go in that direction. Have more respect for readers.', 25705, 0), (428546, 'The respect and protection of woman and of maternity should be raised to the position of an inalienable social duty and should become one of the principles of human morality.', 11408, 0), (428547, 'I''m just trying to approach what I make with as much respect and research as I can, and just make it with a good heart.', 67765, 0), (428548, 'One of the surprising things in this world is the respect a worthless man has for himself.', 13154, 0), (428549, 'May the God of your choice bless and keep you. I respect Him as long as He does not circumcise me anymore.', 3584, 0), (428550, 'I''m like Albert Schweitzer and Bertrand Russell and Albert Einstein in that I have a respect for life - in any form. I believe in nature, in the birds, the sea, the sky, in everything I can see or that there is real evidence for. If these things are what you mean by God, then I believe in God.', 10463, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (428551, 'I think a lot of people have lost respect for the individual, you know, the individual, the person who doesn''t conform.', 964, 0), (428552, 'I want there to be a level of respect between everybody.', 22682, 0), (428553, 'I try to protect my loved ones, the people I share my life with, because they don''t have a public life like me. I want to keep their lives private out of respect for them.', 67766, 0), (428554, 'Sometimes we are separated by differences, and sometimes we are united by common ideals of respect and compassion.', 21274, 0), (428555, 'My father knew my husband long before I ever did. He actually always says that he loved him first... there really was this wonderful respect and admiration between the two of them before I even came into the picture.', 67767, 0), (428556, 'We''re one of the only animals in the world that don''t really think of ourselves as animals, but we are animals, and we must respect our fellow animals.', 5248, 0), (428557, 'Jose Mourinho and I get along well. I''ve lots of respect for him. He gives me a lot of confidence. After a bad game, he dares to say, ''We have played with 10 today,'' but that''s it. At moments like that, he leaves me alone.', 67768, 0), (428558, 'Olympism seeks to create a way of life based on the joy found in effort, the educational value of a good example and respect for universal fundamental ethical principles.', 59474, 0), (428559, 'Become an internationalist and learn to respect all life. Make war on machines. And in particular the sterile machines of corporate death and the robots that guard them.', 10121, 0), (428560, 'Unless India stands up to the world, no one will respect us. In this world, fear has no place. Only strength respects strength.', 1798, 0), (428561, 'Although a lot of pain for a little screen time; Shaving legs, waxing eyebrows, high heels, trying to put on a bra, losing weight because women''s clothes are SO revealing - Ladies you have my respect.', 67413, 0), (428562, 'Throughout the years, many Christian women have told me of their great respect for the bravery and courage evident in my work, perhaps even gesturing to their own Isis earrings or a Nile River Goddess pendants.', 67769, 0), (428563, 'Ardent love or desire introduced, as passionately longing to please and glorify the Divine Being, to be in every respect conformed to him, and in that way to enjoy him.', 67770, 0), (428564, 'Terrorism can never be accepted. We must fight it together, with methods that do not compromise our respect for the rule of law and human rights, or are used as an excuse for others to do so.', 67728, 0), (428565, 'You start to look at it with a deeper respect and I think that deeper respect for what you do builds more self-respect.', 67771, 0), (428566, 'I was silent as a child, and silenced as a young woman; I am taking my lumps and bumps for being a big mouth, now, but usually from those whose opinion I don''t respect.', 26083, 0), (428567, 'As far as more recognition goes, I am happy with the amount of love and respect I have received from other artists and the public. Of course, I would love more, and think I deserve it.', 67772, 0), (428568, 'There was no respect for youth when I was young, and now that I am old, there is no respect for age, I missed it coming and going.', 16669, 0), (428569, 'I will not speak with disrespect of the Republican Party. I always speak with respect of the past.', 1970, 0), (428570, 'But it''s important, while we are supporting lessons in respecting others, to remember that many of our youngest kids need to learn to respect themselves. You learn your worth from the way you are treated.', 1552, 0), (428571, 'Hip-hop is more about attaining wealth. People respect success. They respect big. They don''t even have to like your music. If you''re big enough, people are drawn to you.', 8650, 0), (428572, 'I think the way to keep a friendship is to respect that everybody is different.', 67773, 0), (428573, 'I always remember having a healthy respect for my grandmother.', 67349, 0), (428574, 'I''ll work with a director if I think I''m going to get into a comfortable situation, and if it''s someone I respect and who respects me, even if they''re not so well known. Movies are hard to make, and you have to work toward a common ethic and do your best.', 29124, 0), (428575, 'I think it''s important for artists to work together. It''s great for fans to see, like, Ludacris came out to our show in Atlanta and kinda made a surprise appearance there, it shows a mutual respect for what each other does.', 22996, 0), (428576, 'If you are a card-carrying human being, chances are that you share the same fear as all other humans: the fear of losing love, respect and connection to others. And if you are human, in order to avoid or prevent the pain, trauma and perceived devastation of the loss, you will do anything to avoid your greatest fear from being visited on you.', 634, 0), (428577, 'Why don''t women have respect for themselves nowadays? What happen to the woman who learned her grandmama''s recipes and made her man sweet potato pie? I tell you, they don''t make ''em like they used to. Will my real women stand up, please?', 67774, 0), (428578, 'I have a mentor. I have... guides. I have a lot of guides. Not a lot, but people whose opinions I really respect and who I will turn to.', 47906, 0), (428579, 'If we cannot come together to pause, to respect our dead and the heroic lives of meaning they led, then ours is truly a civilization lost.', 67775, 0), (428580, 'Men secretly respect a woman who is strong, has confidence and has dreams of her own. There''s nothing more attractive to a man than a woman who has dignity and pride in who she is.', 794, 0), (428581, 'The Cobra is my personal favorite car. The original 289 Cobra is the car I respect the most. I like to drive the 289 better than the 427.', 66976, 0), (428582, 'I don''t know where people think I''m from, but I''m from Chicago. It''s really just that. People wanna romanticize it and say, ''There''s two sides to it, and it''s a beautiful love/hate story of violence and music.'' But it''s really just a very scummy place where people don''t have respect for other people''s lives.', 67776, 0), (428583, 'It''s one thing I like about America - they respect the sportsman. They put them up on a pedestal. They don''t try to knock them down. And that''s a great thing, to be respected by the whole country. It''s so patriotic!', 67777, 0), (428584, 'If you respect a language and culture, it shows in your work.', 66442, 0), (428585, 'If we are to build grassroots respect for the institutions and processes that constitute democracy, the state must treat its citizens as real citizens rather than as subjects.', 67778, 0), (428586, 'Being liked by the boys and girls on the bus doesn''t necessarily earn you the respect of the people back home. Standing up to them, giving as good as you get, all that helps.', 66646, 0), (428587, 'Children need teachers who have stars in their eyes themselves and who treat them with respect.', 67779, 0), (428588, 'The only places where I have found that simple human dignity, that respect for the other man, and the gracious feel of tolerance and humanity have not been either among the heroes of the class-struggle or the ''thinking men'' but among my simple ''backward'' people.', 24318, 0), (428589, 'The young people I know judge leaders by their deeds and abhor hypocrisy. Inconsistency and point-scoring do not win respect. It''s not easy to be engaged in political debate when it is reduced to performers trying to outdo each other. Actions from leaders must mirror the values they claim to espouse.', 467, 0), (428590, 'I shall not remind you, Citizen-Directors, of all I have done for the triumph of liberty, the prosperity of St. Domingo, the glory of the French Republic; nor will I protest to you my attachment to our mother country, to my duties; my respect to the constitution, to the laws of the Republic, and my submission to the government.', 67780, 0), (428591, 'I feel lucky that I found my talent, not unlucky that I was born with a disability. When I''m on a horse, I''m more worried about what the riding hat is doing to my hair than what my bent legs and arms are doing. What riding has given me is respect.', 67781, 0), (428592, 'There is no, and cannot be, any situation in which we don''t respect the law and the judiciary. It is unacceptable to attack the courts; criticism is allowed, but attacks are not. It shakes the basis of our democracy.', 67025, 0), (428593, 'Prince was one of the best people I''ve met. He didn''t care about the big system. I was always like, at any time, Prince could write a No. 1 song because he''s that talented, but he chooses to do what he wants. I respect that. He actually helped me through a lot of situations with his knowledge.', 3263, 0), (428594, 'I watched my parents act as completely equal partners in their relationship, and as a son to a woman I respect immensely, I never thought of gender inequality as a child.', 66612, 0), (428595, 'I think that in any language when you have a real relationship, and there is love and respect between people, infidelity is always something difficult to accept - whether you are Chinese, British, French. I think that is a universal concept... or problem.', 66933, 0), (428596, 'Find your self-respect now. Don''t dumb yourselves down. Think of yourself as capable and worthy of finding a guy who is going to respect you, too. It''s so important, I mean, and the confidence you get from feeling smart and tackling something like mathematics, which is a challenge, right? Math is hard.', 66799, 0), (428597, 'It is not likely that posterity will fall in love with us, but not impossible that it may respect or sympathize; so a man would rather leave behind him the portrait of his spirit than a portrait of his face.', 449, 0), (428598, 'Respect for the fragility and importance of an individual life is still the mark of an educated man.', 7782, 0), (428599, 'Respect is the word I want. You have to earn it. You give, and you get it in return, that''s how I see it.', 63097, 0), (428600, 'The authority of a life for Christ always has greater influence than the authority of talking. A young person can possess all of the benefits of authority - influence, respect, and strength - just by following Jesus wherever he leads.', 16455, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (428601, 'It''s not that the Irish are cynical. It''s rather that they have a wonderful lack of respect for everything and everybody.', 9701, 0), (428602, 'More than in any other performing arts the lack of respect for acting seems to spring from the fact that every layman considers himself a valid critic.', 1662, 0), (428603, 'Treating your adversary with respect is striking soft in battle.', 2087, 0), (428604, 'The basic Buddhist stand on the question of equality between the genders is age-old. At the highest tantric levels, at the highest esoteric level, you must respect women: every woman.', 5025, 0), (428605, 'I respect coaches I respect what good coaches do. I know that you don''t learn to be a coach in an hour and a half. ', 13024, 0), (428606, 'I''m fiercely patriotic, and the flag and the anthem is something that I really, really respect.', 67372, 0), (428607, 'I owe my success to having listened respectfully to the very best advice, and then going away and doing the exact opposite.', 67663, 0), (428608, 'I always respect a woman.', 65079, 0), (428609, 'As all human beings are, in my view, creatures of God''s design, we must respect all other human beings. That does not mean I have to agree with their choices or agree with their opinions, but indeed I respect them as human beings.', 67782, 0), (428610, 'I respect the view of a rating agency, but I do not make a budget for the rating agency. I make a budget for the people of India.', 67783, 0), (428611, 'It is hard to feel individually responsible with respect to the invisible processes of a huge and distant government.', 11471, 0), (428612, 'I respect only those who resist me, but I cannot tolerate them.', 11599, 0), (428613, 'To be loved at first sight, a man should have at the same time something to respect and something to pity in his face.', 952, 0), (428614, 'I adore adverbs they are the only qualifications I really much respect. ', 561, 0), (42