've remained close with Simon Fuller. Working as executive producer on ''American idol'' for its first seven years not only was an inspirational journey into the heart of American pop culture, it opened my eyes to the untapped potential of the incredibly dynamic young people in this world.', 68055, 0), (429372, 'I am never without my lyric book. If anything inspirational happens, I have it there so nothing''s forgotten.', 47040, 0), (429373, 'I grew up in a bookless house - my parents didn''t read poetry, so if I hadn''t had the chance to experience it at school I''d never have experienced it. But I loved English, and I was very lucky in that I had inspirational English teachers, Miss Scriven and Mr. Walker, and they liked us to learn poems by heart, which I found I loved doing.', 7418, 0), (429374, 'I''d like to one day be featured on a list of inspirational people who have made a difference in the world, whether it be helping underprivileged people or putting an end to the poaching of wildlife in Africa.', 68056, 0), (429375, 'I love a lot of the New York bands, but Patti Smith stands out. I just read ''Just Kids'' and it''s an inspirational, well-written account of an emerging New York artist in the late seventies.', 68057, 0), (429376, 'The government will see that human spaceflight is useful - for science and the economy - and inspirational.', 68058, 0), (429377, 'I''m a gay disabled man who has become very successful. I don''t get up in the morning and think I''m inspirational I just get up thinking that I love horses. ', 67781, 0), (429378, 'Inside, I''ve got a real purist desire and dream about the music. I like the idea of being able to carve out a kind of magical, colourful, artistic, inspirational life. And the reality just turns out to be quite different, working with the business to bring this thing you have created into the world.', 22702, 0), (429379, 'The best form of flattery is to be admired, imitated or respected. I''ve always felt proud our fans look up to us or feel we are inspirational.', 67179, 0), (429380, 'Nothing makes one feel so strong as a call for help.', 3779, 0), (429381, 'Our ideals are our better selves.', 13866, 0), (429382, 'I hope that at the end of the seven years, people will say that I have been of some inspirational value to them at home in terms of inclusiveness and abroad, I look forward to representing Ireland.', 67754, 0), (429383, 'I do a lot of inspirational talks for kids, to motivate them to change their lives and give them hope.', 68059, 0), (429384, 'I had an inspirational teacher at my junior school: Peter Nixon. He was enthusiastic, knowledgeable and slightly scary - a good combination for a teacher.', 68060, 0), (429385, 'My tastes and inspirational artists were always rather eclectic and diverse.', 68061, 0), (429386, 'We all obviously need others to look up to, and be inspirational to us. Ford did a great job as far as putting the presidency back where it belonged, getting the trust back after Nixon. And President Reagan has been one of the most influential presidents.', 68062, 0), (429387, 'I pull a lot of the stuff that I play off the rhythm tracks - and Keith Richards has been one of the main contributors to my inspirational playing.', 68063, 0), (429388, 'I would probably work with Drake as he is massively inspirational to me as a writer as well as an artist. If not him, then Susan Boyle!', 68064, 0), (429389, 'I''m very fond of the British cinema. I''m a big fan of Martin Campbell and Daniel Craig. I actually find Daniel very inspirational, especially on the physical side of things. He really inspired me to get back into shape when I started to add on a few pounds. I think he''s a great role model.', 68065, 0), (429390, 'I grew up in a very spiritual home in a Liberty City neighborhood of Miami, FL. I was raised in the church, and my mother was a very inspirational person in my life.', 68066, 0), (429391, 'My father, Oliver Hynes, was an educator. He was originally just a teacher, a very good one, but then he was promoted to be in charge of education for the entire area. He was always an inspirational teacher. He was my big personal supporter, always coming here for the Tony Awards. My mother, Carmel, was a homemaker.', 68067, 0), (429392, 'Architecture is not an inspirational business, it''s a rational procedure to do sensible and hopefully beautiful things; that''s all.', 68068, 0), (429393, 'I''ve done a lot of albums and I kinda know when I''m onto something that was inspirational for me to record and create, and this was one of those projects where I really enjoyed making the album.', 68069, 0), (429394, 'Thelonious Monk was one of the musicians I most connected with early on. I''m a huge Betty Carter fan, and the way that Abbey Lincoln and Shirley Horn grew immensely from the time they were young is so inspirational.', 68070, 0), (429395, 'On the recollection of so many and great favours and blessings, I now, with a high sense of gratitude, presume to offer up my sincere thanks to the Almighty, the Creator and Preserver.', 68071, 0), (429396, 'I think that''s a great opportunity, to pick a script where you can build up a good skill. I think the main thing I look for when I look at scripts is if it''s inspirational. If it''s something that teenagers can relate to. And is it something that the audience is going to get something out of. If not, then it''s really not worth doing.', 68072, 0), (429397, 'I view art as an inspirational tool.', 68073, 0), (429398, 'I do like alternative rock and rap, but as far as inspirational, then I go full-on orchestra. It fills up your entire being.', 68074, 0), (429399, 'I want to be an inspirational model. I want people to look at me and say, ''Wow, she looks healthy.''', 68075, 0), (429400, 'I want to be motivational and inspirational for everybody: my big aim is more women on bicycles.', 68076, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429401, 'You always draw inspiration from your family or your parents if they''ve proven to be inspirational. My mother is someone who''s always been inspirational to me.', 68077, 0), (429402, 'I love inspirational R&B, like Mary J. Blige and Jennifer Hudson. I want to do that. That kind of music stays with you.', 68078, 0), (429403, 'I wrote ''(''Til) I Kissed You'' about a girl I met in Australia. Her name was Lilian, and she was very, very inspirational. I was married, but... I wrote the song about her on the way back home.', 68079, 0), (429404, 'We''ve been surrounded by images of space our whole lives, from the speculative images of science fiction to the inspirational visions of artists to the increasingly beautiful pictures made possible by complex technologies. But whilst we have an overwhelmingly vivid visual understanding of space, we have no sense of what space sounds like.', 68080, 0), (429405, 'Think with your whole body.', 3264, 0), (429406, 'There have been many different artists that have been inspirational. I suppose the question is directed to what was the reason why I went into fantasy illustration.', 68081, 0), (429407, 'Lee''s great gifts are teaching and inspirational guidance, not administration and management.', 68082, 0), (429408, 'A dream doesn''t become reality through magic; it takes sweat, determination and hard work.', 1749, 0), (429409, 'Keep your dreams alive. Understand to achieve anything requires faith and belief in yourself, vision, hard work, determination, and dedication. Remember all things are possible for those who believe.', 42279, 0), (429410, 'Stay true to yourself, yet always be open to learn. Work hard, and never give up on your dreams, even when nobody else believes they can come true but you. These are not cliches but real tools you need no matter what you do in life to stay focused on your path.', 68083, 0), (429411, 'The biggest adventure you can take is to live the life of your dreams.', 588, 0), (429412, 'Deep into that darkness peering, long I stood there, wondering, fearing, doubting, dreaming dreams no mortal ever dared to dream before.', 49, 0), (429413, 'Follow your passion, be prepared to work hard and sacrifice, and, above all, don''t let anyone limit your dreams.', 26017, 0), (429414, 'Stay focused, go after your dreams and keep moving toward your goals.', 68084, 0), (429415, 'Remember your dreams and fight for them. You must know what you want from life. There is just one thing that makes your dream become impossible: the fear of failure.', 34, 0), (429416, 'Consult not your fears but your hopes and your dreams. Think not about your frustrations, but about your unfulfilled potential. Concern yourself not with what you tried and failed in, but with what it is still possible for you to do.', 4433, 0), (429417, 'Trust in dreams, for in them is hidden the gate to eternity.', 5542, 0), (429418, 'New Year''s Day. A fresh start. A new chapter in life waiting to be written. New questions to be asked, embraced, and loved. Answers to be discovered and then lived in this transformative year of delight and self-discovery. Today carve out a quiet interlude for yourself in which to dream, pen in hand. Only dreams give birth to change.', 7175, 0), (429419, 'I like the dreams of the future better than the history of the past.', 1207, 0), (429420, 'Never give up on what you really want to do. The person with big dreams is more powerful than the one with all the facts.', 63634, 0), (429421, 'Follow your dreams, believe in yourself and don''t give up.', 15818, 0), (429422, 'Yesterday is but today''s memory, and tomorrow is today''s dream.', 5542, 0), (429423, 'Sleep is the best meditation.', 5025, 0), (429424, 'I couldn''t find the sports car of my dreams, so I built it myself.', 68085, 0), (429425, 'I''m a dreamer. I have to dream and reach for the stars, and if I miss a star then I grab a handful of clouds.', 11133, 0), (429426, 'Help others achieve their dreams and you will achieve yours.', 1873, 0), (429427, 'Education is not a tool for development - individual, community and the nation. It is the foundation for our future. It is empowerment to make choices and emboldens the youth to chase their dreams.', 68086, 0), (429428, 'Reality is wrong. Dreams are for real.', 1097, 0), (429429, 'A city is not gauged by its length and width, but by the broadness of its vision and the height of its dreams.', 59745, 0), (429430, 'Grit is that ''extra something'' that separates the most successful people from the rest. It''s the passion, perseverance, and stamina that we must channel in order to stick with our dreams until they become a reality.', 68087, 0), (429431, 'Let your dreams outgrow the shoes of your expectations.', 68088, 0), (429432, 'Your vision will become clear only when you can look into your own heart. Who looks outside, dreams; who looks inside, awakes.', 28934, 0), (429433, 'I dream of painting and then I paint my dream.', 89, 0), (429434, 'You control your future, your destiny. What you think about comes about. By recording your dreams and goals on paper, you set in motion the process of becoming the person you most want to be. Put your future in good hands - your own.', 68089, 0), (429435, 'Through hard work, perseverance and a faith in God, you can live your dreams.', 1793, 0), (429436, 'A horse is the projection of peoples'' dreams about themselves - strong, powerful, beautiful - and it has the capability of giving us escape from our mundane existence.', 15447, 0), (429437, 'In my dreams, I could be a Princess, and that''s what I was. Like most little girls, I believed nothing less than a Prince could make my dreams come true.', 44815, 0), (429438, 'The only thing that comes to a sleeping man is dreams.', 1097, 0), (429439, 'All men dream, but not equally. Those who dream by night in the dusty recesses of their minds, wake in the day to find that it was vanity: but the dreamers of the day are dangerous men, for they may act on their dreams with open eyes, to make them possible.', 16259, 0), (429440, 'We all have our time machines. Some take us back, they''re called memories. Some take us forward, they''re called dreams.', 68090, 0), (429441, 'Great dreams of great dreamers are always transcended.', 1798, 0), (429442, 'Keep true to the dreams of your youth.', 1988, 0), (429443, 'The path from dreams to success does exist. May you have the vision to find it, the courage to get on to it, and the perseverance to follow it.', 68091, 0), (429444, 'So to all Americans, in every city near and far, small and large, from mountain to mountain, and from ocean to ocean, hear these words: You will never be ignored again. Your voice, your hopes, and your dreams will define our American destiny. And your courage and goodness and love will forever guide us along the way.', 64643, 0), (429445, 'A dreamer is one who can only find his way by moonlight, and his punishment is that he sees the dawn before the rest of the world.', 40, 0), (429446, 'Job training empowers people to realize their dreams and improve their lives.', 68092, 0), (429447, 'Follow your dreams, work hard, practice and persevere. Make sure you eat a variety of foods, get plenty of exercise and maintain a healthy lifestyle.', 68093, 0), (429448, 'Take a leap of faith and begin this wondrous new year by believing. Believe in yourself. And believe that there is a loving Source - a Sower of Dreams - just waiting to be asked to help you make your dreams come true.', 7175, 0), (429449, 'We live between the act of awakening and the act of surrender. Each morning, we awaken to the light and the invitation to a new day in the world of time; each night, we surrender to the dark to be taken to play in the world of dreams where time is no more.', 400, 0), (429450, 'Never underestimate the power of dreams and the influence of the human spirit. We are all the same in this notion: The potential for greatness lives within each of us.', 60458, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429451, 'We have to stand up for what we believe in, even when we might not be popular for it. Honesty starts with being ourselves, authentic and true to who we are and what we believe in, and that may not always be popular, but it will always let you follow your dreams and your heart.', 66932, 0), (429452, 'I dreamed I was a butterfly, flitting around in the sky; then I awoke. Now I wonder: Am I a man who dreamt of being a butterfly, or am I a butterfly dreaming that I am a man?', 2480, 0), (429453, 'Never set limits, go after your dreams, don''t be afraid to push the boundaries. And laugh a lot - it''s good for you!', 68094, 0), (429454, 'If you want to have a life that is worth living, a life that expresses your deepest feelings and emotions and cares and dreams, you have to fight for it.', 753, 0), (429455, 'My imagination completely controls me, and forever feeds the fire that burns with dark red light in my heart by bringing me the best dreams. I''ve always had a wild imagination, a big heart and a tortured soul so I feel that dark fantasy, love and horror are in my blood.', 68095, 0), (429456, 'We are such stuff as dreams are made on and our little life is rounded with a sleep. ', 13, 0), (429457, 'It was one of my dreams as a child, growing up in my little village with my cousins. We used to walk together, and I used to say, when you look at the world map, ''This town is there, that town is there, that river is there.'' I used to say, ''One day, I''m going to travel these places.''', 68096, 0), (429458, 'Without leaps of imagination, or dreaming, we lose the excitement of possibilities. Dreaming, after all, is a form of planning.', 1739, 0), (429459, 'We become not a melting pot but a beautiful mosaic. Different people, different beliefs, different yearnings, different hopes, different dreams.', 1229, 0), (429460, 'My dreams for the future are simple: work, a happy, healthy family, a lovely long motorcycle ride, and continuing the struggle to awaken people to the need for serious human rights reform.', 68097, 0), (429461, 'I always feel like it''s two key ingredients when it comes to following your dreams, making something happen that the average person deems difficult. If you truly believe it, that''s step one. Step two, is, you know, the hard work that goes along with it.', 60269, 0), (429462, 'I would encourage you to set really high goals. Set goals that, when you set them, you think they''re impossible. But then every day you can work towards them, and anything is possible, so keep working hard and follow your dreams.', 68098, 0), (429463, 'The equal right of all citizens to health, education, work, food, security, culture, science, and wellbeing - that is, the same rights we proclaimed when we began our struggle, in addition to those which emerge from our dreams of justice and equality for all inhabitants of our world - is what I wish for all.', 3470, 0), (429464, 'Long walks on the beach are the supposed holy grail of a romantic evening. The beach becomes a kind of utopia - the place where all our dreams come true.', 9530, 0), (429465, 'Who looks outside, dreams; who looks inside, awakes.', 28934, 0), (429466, 'The interpretation of dreams is the royal road to a knowledge of the unconscious activities of the mind.', 555, 0), (429467, 'Visions are worth fighting for. Why spend your life making someone else''s dreams?', 792, 0), (429468, 'Dreams are the seeds of change. Nothing ever grows without a seed, and nothing ever changes without a dream.', 68099, 0), (429469, 'Never let life impede on your ability to manifest your dreams. Dig deeper into your dreams and deeper into yourself and believe that anything is possible, and make it happen.', 67919, 0), (429470, 'When all of your wishes are granted, many of your dreams will be destroyed.', 2519, 0), (429471, 'Computers are magnificent tools for the realization of our dreams, but no machine can replace the human spark of spirit, compassion, love, and understanding.', 66684, 0), (429472, 'There''s nothing as exciting as a comeback - seeing someone with dreams, watching them fail, and then getting a second chance.', 68100, 0), (429473, 'I don''t think you should spend your life praying for things, but I do believe you should thank God for what He''s given you... but I think the scripture teaches us that we can pray for our dreams, pray for the big things... he''s not a small God; this God is incredible.', 3956, 0), (429474, 'Why does the eye see a thing more clearly in dreams than the imagination when awake?', 1386, 0), (429475, 'Don''t give up on your dreams, or your dreams will give up on you.', 1721, 0), (429476, 'Dreams about the future are always filled with gadgets.', 404, 0), (429477, 'I learned to dream through reading, learned to create dreams through writing, and learned to develop dreamers through teaching. I shall always be a dreamer. Come dream with me.', 68101, 0), (429478, 'The only time you really live fully is from thirty to sixty. The young are slaves to dreams the old servants of regrets. Only the middle-aged have all their five senses in the keeping of their wits. ', 1674, 0), (429479, 'If you take responsibility for yourself you will develop a hunger to accomplish your dreams.', 1873, 0), (429480, 'It''s insecurity that is always chasing you and standing in the way of your dreams.', 68102, 0), (429481, 'I have dreams of becoming a professional pastry chef and having a little bakery - that''s how much I love baking. I love to cook in general, but my heart lies in desserts.', 68103, 0), (429482, 'In my dreams and visions, I seemed to see a line, and on the other side of that line were green fields, and lovely flowers, and beautiful white ladies, who stretched out their arms to me over the line, but I couldn''t reach them no-how. I always fell before I got to the line.', 1799, 0), (429483, 'To accomplish great things, we must not only act, but also dream; not only plan, but also believe.', 348, 0), (429484, 'I don''t design clothes, I design dreams.', 8463, 0), (429485, 'If one advances confidently in the direction of his dreams, and endeavors to live the life which he has imagined, he will meet with a success unexpected in common hours.', 1049, 0), (429486, 'I think everyone dreams of that nice romantic wedding.', 68104, 0), (429487, 'The greatest achievement was at first and for a time a dream. The oak sleeps in the acorn, the bird waits in the egg, and in the highest vision of the soul a waking angel stirs. Dreams are the seedlings of realities.', 2970, 0), (429488, 'I''ll let you be in my dreams if I can be in yours.', 289, 0), (429489, 'Be a dreamer. If you don''t know how to dream, you''re dead.', 756, 0), (429490, 'If there are dreams about a beautiful South Africa, there are also roads that lead to their goal. Two of these roads could be named Goodness and Forgiveness.', 1722, 0), (429491, 'Passion isn''t something that lives way up in the sky, in abstract dreams and hopes. It lives at ground level, in the specific details of what you''re actually doing every day.', 35133, 0), (429492, 'The life of a man consists not in seeing visions and in dreaming dreams, but in active charity and in willing service.', 147, 0), (429493, 'Believe in love. Believe in magic. Hell, believe in Santa Clause. Believe in others. Believe in yourself. Believe in your dreams. If you don''t, who will?', 2385, 0), (429494, 'Follow your dreams. If you have a goal, and you want to achieve it, then work hard and do everything you can to get there, and one day it will come true.', 68105, 0), (429495, 'The world needs dreamers and the world needs doers. But above all, the world needs dreamers who do.', 7175, 0), (429496, 'Education is at the heart of achieving your dreams.', 68106, 0), (429497, 'Lose your dreams and you might lose your mind.', 20225, 0), (429498, 'What is life? A madness. What is life? An illusion, a shadow, a story. And the greatest good is little enough; for all life is a dream, and dreams themselves are only dreams.', 84, 0), (429499, 'Hold fast to dreams For when dreams go Life is a barren field Frozen with snow.', 1009, 0), (429500, 'Follow your dreams and use your natural-born talents and skills to make this a better world for tomorrow.', 21274, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429501, 'Take, if you must, this little bag of dreams, Unloose the cord, and they will wrap you round.', 62867, 0), (429502, 'Make treating yourself a priority and always remember your life is happening now. Don''t put off all your dreams and pleasures to another day. In any balanced personal definition of success there has to be a powerful element of living life in the present.', 43841, 0), (429503, 'I have dreamed in my life, dreams that have stayed with me ever after, and changed my ideas; they have gone through and through me, like wine through water, and altered the color of my mind.', 55, 0), (429504, 'I''m very comfortable with the nature of life and death, and that we come to an end. What''s most difficult to imagine is that those dreams and early yearnings and desires of childhood and adolescence will also disappear. But who knows? Maybe you become part of the eternal whatever.', 38121, 0), (429505, 'We need time to defuse, to contemplate. Just as in sleep our brains relax and give us dreams, so at some time in the day we need to disconnect, reconnect, and look around us.', 29880, 0), (429506, 'Don''t let the winds blow your dreams away... or steal your faith in God.', 67364, 0), (429507, 'There something to be said for having even unrealistic dreams. Even if the dreams don''t come true - that, to me, is what''s beautiful about Los Angeles. It''s full of these people who have moved there to chase these dreams.', 25814, 0), (429508, 'Some people ask why people would go into a dark room to be scared. I say they are already scared, and they need to have that fear manipulated and massaged. I think of horror movies as the disturbed dreams of a society.', 68107, 0), (429509, 'In dreams, anything can be anything, and everybody can do. We can fly, we can turn upside down, we can transform into anything.', 7842, 0), (429510, 'If you don''t have dreams, you don''t have a life.', 67886, 0), (429511, 'Flying dreams mean that you''re doing the right thing with your life.', 1002, 0), (429512, 'Myths are public dreams, dreams are private myths.', 1123, 0), (429513, 'I''ve always followed my heart and pursued my dreams, and I imagine that people find that inspiring. I hope that is the effect I have on my fans and people in general. I definitely want to project a positive energy out into the world.', 13881, 0), (429514, 'I''m sick of following my dreams. I''m just going to ask them where they''re goin'', and hook up with them later.', 27687, 0), (429515, 'When you have little girls bringing you your action figures for you to sign, it''s like, ''Wow, things are happening, and dreams do come true.''', 67740, 0), (429516, 'Follow your dreams. Just make sure to have fun too.', 55068, 0), (429517, 'The American Dream has run out of gas. The car has stopped. It no longer supplies the world with its images, its dreams, its fantasies. No more. It''s over. It supplies the world with its nightmares now: the Kennedy assassination, Watergate, Vietnam.', 2312, 0), (429518, 'People are so busy dreaming the American Dream, fantasizing about what they could be or have a right to be, that they''re all asleep at the switch. Consequently we are living in the Age of Human Error.', 18125, 0), (429519, 'I don''t remember my dreams too much. I hardly have ever gotten ideas from nighttime dreams. But I love daydreaming and dream logic and the way dreams go.', 18666, 0), (429520, 'People with disabilities have abilities too and that is what this course is all about - making sure those abilities blossom and shine so that all the dreams you have can come true.', 68108, 0), (429521, 'When I grew up, I only had two dreams. One was to be a cowboy and another was to be in the military. I grew up extremely patriotic and riding horses.', 2455, 0), (429522, 'When a person starts to talk about their dreams, it''s as if something bubbles up from within. Their eyes brighten, their face glows, and you can feel the excitement in their words.', 1810, 0), (429523, 'Our life is composed greatly from dreams, from the unconscious, and they must be brought into connection with action. They must be woven together.', 23, 0), (429524, 'Everyone loves a comeback story, and everyone loves the underdog as well. I kind of feel like I''ve been the underdog. Hopefully that inspires people to not give up on themselves and their lives and not give up on their dreams.', 67759, 0), (429525, 'Never in my wildest dreams did I entertain the idea that I would become a fashion designer.', 68109, 0), (429526, 'I feel like, big city or small town, you can relate to following your parents'' footsteps or putting your own dreams on the back burner or vices that we get caught up in - that whole cycle. That''s not just a small-town thing. That''s a life thing.', 68110, 0), (429527, 'When the legends die, the dreams end; there is no more greatness.', 35521, 0), (429528, 'I want to show everyone that if you pursue your dreams, they can come true no matter what. That''s what I want to do.', 68111, 0), (429529, 'I want to create an economy where minimum wage is a very brief stepping stone to higher-paying jobs so people can realize their dreams.', 68112, 0), (429530, 'The world of men is dreaming, it has gone mad in its sleep, and a snake is strangling it, but it can''t wake up.', 178, 0), (429531, 'Divorce is a time of change. It really rocks a foundation of most people''s lives. When we have our heart broken or our dreams taken away from us, it is a time of growth and change.', 5671, 0), (429532, 'It''s when children are 15, 16 or 17 that they decide whether they want to be a doctor, an engineer, a politician or go to the Mars or moon. That is the time they start having a dream, and that''s the time you can work on them. You can help them shape their dreams.', 1798, 0), (429533, 'It is better to risk starving to death then surrender. If you give up on your dreams, what''s left?', 14367, 0), (429534, 'They thought I was a Surrealist, but I wasn''t. I never painted dreams. I painted my own reality.', 1759, 0), (429535, 'The world is full of people who have dreams of playing at Carnegie Hall, of running a marathon, and of owning their own business. The difference between the people who make it across the finish line and everyone else is one simple thing: an action plan.', 68113, 0), (429536, 'The dreams and passions stored within hearts are powerful keys which can unlock a wealth of potential.', 1810, 0), (429537, 'People ask how can a Jewish kid from the Bronx do preppy clothes? Does it have to do with class and money? It has to do with dreams.', 8463, 0), (429538, 'And whether a child is born in the urban sprawl of Detroit or the windswept plains of Nebraska, they look up at the same night sky, they fill their heart with the same dreams, and they are infused with the breath of life by the same almighty Creator.', 64643, 0), (429539, 'I think that they way my parents raised me, they taught me to always follow my dreams and never give up, no matter what the obstacle.', 68114, 0), (429540, 'Never think you can''t do something. I definitely never thought I could write a book, and even after I started writing it, I was like, ''Oh my God, how am I gonna write a book?'' Just set your sights high and reach for the stars. Go live your dreams, and never think you can''t.', 1916, 0), (429541, 'I believe dreams represent the purest form of fantasy we unleash through our subconscious. They represent the truest freedom we can experience. Totally unrepressed and totally creative.', 68115, 0), (429542, 'In my long life I have found peace, joy, and happiness beyond my fondest hopes and dreams. One of the supreme benedictions of my life has been my marriage to an elect daughter of God. I love her with all my heart and soul.', 9153, 0), (429543, 'We all have so much more power to make our dreams a reality - and love life along the way - than we think we do!', 68116, 0), (429544, 'Tread softly because you tread on my dreams.', 62867, 0), (429545, 'We must stop talking about the American dream and start listening to the dreams of Americans.', 17074, 0), (429546, 'You have to keep going and pursue your dreams.', 68117, 0), (429547, 'He was a dreamer, a thinker, a speculative philosopher... or, as his wife would have it, an idiot.', 386, 0), (429548, 'I prefer to be a dreamer among the humblest, with visions to be realized, than lord among those without dreams and desires.', 5542, 0), (429549, 'Vision gets the dreams started. Dreaming employs your God-given imagination to reinforce the vision. Both are part of something I believe is absolutely necessary to building the life of a champion, a winner, a person of high character who is consistently at the top of whatever game he or she is in.', 68118, 0), (429550, 'I have mixed feelings about how fast things are changing as a result of technology. There''s no denying that through technology there are amazing things being created that help people with diseases or help people''s dreams come true. But there''s also this obsession. Social media is the most dangerous of them all.', 68119, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429551, 'To be given the opportunity to help shape new artists'' careers and mentor them to see their dreams come to fruition is a task I welcome with open arms.', 11155, 0), (429552, 'There are many talented people who haven''t fulfilled their dreams because they over thought it, or they were too cautious, and were unwilling to make the leap of faith.', 3628, 0), (429553, 'Dreams grow if you grow.', 1692, 0), (429554, 'You have to have a dream so you can get up in the morning.', 22666, 0), (429555, 'Strivers achieve what dreamers believe.', 68120, 0), (429556, 'I have had dreams and I have had nightmares, but I have conquered my nightmares because of my dreams.', 4728, 0), (429557, 'As I''ve grown - dare I say it - older, I had hopes of indulging my dreams of being a sailor.', 55927, 0), (429558, 'You have all the reason in the world to achieve your grandest dreams. Imagination plus innovation equals realization.', 1391, 0), (429559, 'Without peace, all other dreams vanish and are reduced to ashes.', 8325, 0), (429560, 'I can''t remember any dreams in my life. There''s so much strange in real life that it often seems like a dream.', 792, 0), (429561, 'Let us keep the dance of rain our fathers kept and tread our dreams beneath the jungle sky.', 68121, 0), (429562, 'I know it''s cliche to say, ''When you do something you love you never work a day in your life.'' But it is true: When you do something you love, life gets to be a little bit easier and enjoyable. So I just want people to follow their dreams.', 68122, 0), (429563, 'You know, one of my biggest dreams in life is to play a Disney princess.', 68123, 0), (429564, 'I''m not really that girl who dreams about her wedding day.', 100, 0), (429565, 'Believe it or not, lots of people change their majors and abandon their dreams just to avoid a couple of math classes in college.', 66799, 0), (429566, 'Do I feel any pressure as the most decorated Winter Olympian in American history? None at all. The only pressures that I know I face are those of how to pay it forward: How can I continually make a positive impact in people''s lives, help others achieve their dreams, create their own Olympic mindset, creating champions within themselves?', 68124, 0), (429567, 'When I am president, I will work to ensure that all of our kids are treated equally and protected equally. Every action I take, I will ask myself, ''Does this make life better for young Americans in Baltimore, Chicago, Detroit, Ferguson, who have as much of a right to live out their dreams as any other child America?''', 64643, 0), (429568, 'The first ''D'' is to dream: dream big - not for yourself, but for the country and for the world. The second ''D'' is to discover: discover your full potential and the opportunities that surround you; and the third ''D'' is to do. ''Do'' means to act on your dreams and make best use of the opportunities you have discovered.', 68125, 0), (429569, 'My dreams were all my own I accounted for them to nobody they were my refuge when annoyed - my dearest pleasure when free. ', 68126, 0), (429570, 'Youth is a wonderful thing. What a crime to waste it on children.', 266, 0), (429571, 'Ideologies separate us. Dreams and anguish bring us together.', 2291, 0), (429572, 'I felt like an ugly duckling back in school. I was a complete tomboy with short hair. Never in my dreams did I imagine that I would walk the ramp with 6-inch heels. My friends can''t believe that I''m an actor, because I was such an introvert in school.', 68127, 0), (429573, 'I feel like I''m making a difference. I feel like putting out a message for young girls to follow your dreams and just work at what you want to do and be yourself.', 67371, 0), (429574, 'Dreams are true while they last, and do we not live in dreams?', 63203, 0), (429575, 'I am a dreamer. Seriously, I''m living on another planet.', 68128, 0), (429576, 'The starting point of discovering who you are, your gifts, your talents, your dreams, is being comfortable with yourself. Spend time alone. Write in a journal. Take long walks in the woods.', 1172, 0), (429577, 'Jazz to me is a living music. It''s a music that since its beginning has expressed the feelings, the dreams, hopes, of the people.', 68129, 0), (429578, 'I mean, every child at one stage dreams of being a prince or a princess.', 68130, 0), (429579, 'We must look for ways to be an active force in our own lives. We must take charge of our own destinies, design a life of substance and truly begin to live our dreams.', 1873, 0), (429580, 'She still talks to me now, only now she talks to me in my dreams. And I can''t wait to go to sleep tonight because we have a lot to talk about. I love you.', 68131, 0), (429581, 'Today I know that there is still work to be done, but along the way my I am achieving my dreams.', 68132, 0), (429582, 'High achievers spot rich opportunities swiftly, make big decisions quickly and move into action immediately. Follow these principles and you can make your dreams come true.', 1935, 0), (429583, 'I am quite a dreamer. I think we all are dreamers. We all don''t like to live a practical life all the time. There is a thin line between our hopes and dreams.', 68133, 0), (429584, 'Winners, I am convinced, imagine their dreams first. They want it with all their heart and expect it to come true. There is, I believe, no other way to live.', 67821, 0), (429585, 'The dreams which reveal the supernatural are promises and messages that God sends us directly: they are nothing but His angels, His ministering spirits, who usually appear to us when we are in a great predicament.', 2652, 0), (429586, 'A runner must run with dreams in his heart, not money in his pocket.', 67355, 0), (429587, 'It is in our idleness, in our dreams, that the submerged truth sometimes comes to the top.', 113, 0), (429588, 'I couldn''t help but to think back to my classmates at Thomas Jefferson High School in San Antonio. They had the same talent, the same brains, the same dreams as the folks we sat with at Stanford and Harvard. I realized the difference wasn''t one of intelligence or drive. The difference was opportunity.', 68134, 0), (429589, 'I want people to follow their dreams, yes... but I''m not interested in telling young black kids how to be rappers... I want to show them that there''s so many other paths you can take, besides a rapper or basketball player.', 60269, 0), (429590, 'You have to keep pushing toward those dreams no matter what setbacks happen.', 60646, 0), (429591, 'I just write what I wanted to write. I write what amuses me. It''s totally for myself. I never in my wildest dreams expected this popularity.', 28, 0), (429592, 'There are millions of Americans outside Washington who are tired of stale political arguments and are moving this country forward. They believe, and I believe, that here in America, our success should depend not on accident of birth, but the strength of our work ethic and the scope of our dreams.', 1693, 0), (429593, 'Romantic comedies seem to take over where the fairytales of childhood left off, feeding our dreams of a soulmate; though, sadly, the Hollywood endings prove quite elusive in the real world.', 67020, 0), (429594, 'Saddle your dreams before you ride em.', 21572, 0), (429595, 'Sometimes, the only realists are the dreamers.', 43395, 0), (429596, 'I paint what cannot be photographed, that which comes from the imagination or from dreams, or from an unconscious drive.', 10263, 0), (429597, 'My life turned out to be beyond my greatest dreams.', 48587, 0), (429598, 'Dreams do come true. If anyone''s proof of that, it''s me.', 68135, 0), (429599, 'I suppose all fictional characters, especially in adventure or heroic fiction, at the end of the day are our dreams about ourselves. And sometimes they can be really revealing.', 1001, 0), (429600, 'One of the dreams on my wish list is to spend more time in Thailand.', 68136, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429601, 'In bed my real love has always been the sleep that rescued me by allowing me to dream.', 23247, 0), (429602, 'Ever since I was a kid, I wanted to be a marine biologist. As you go through the grind and the distraction of a career, it''s easy to lose sight of your dreams.', 55738, 0), (429603, 'I''m a big believer in living out your dreams and facing your fears.', 68137, 0), (429604, 'Men are the dreams of a shadow.', 16113, 0), (429605, 'All my life, I''ve had these flashbacks, these dreams, nightmares, daymares, like visions, where I relive certain plays. Only the bad plays. I see them over and over, as if somebody''s rewinding a tape and forcing me to watch.', 66725, 0), (429606, 'There''s a lot of blood, sweat, and guts between dreams and success.', 67991, 0), (429607, 'Working together in concert more smoothly not only helps us move more quickly; it changes the nature of what we can undertake. When we have the confidence that we can orchestrate the group effort required to realize them, we dare bigger dreams.', 68138, 0), (429608, 'Short stories are tiny windows into other worlds and other minds and dreams. They are journeys you can make to the far side of the universe and still be back in time for dinner.', 14, 0), (429609, 'What is a television apparatus to man, who has only to shut his eyes to see the most inaccessible regions of the seen and the never seen, who has only to imagine in order to pierce through walls and cause all the planetary Baghdads of his dreams to rise from the dust.', 1803, 0), (429610, 'Of all our dreams today there is none more important - or so hard to realise - than that of peace in the world. May we never lose our faith in it or our resolve to do everything that can be done to convert it one day into reality.', 17580, 0), (429611, 'You can do anything if you set your mind to it. Look out for kids, help them dream and be inspired. We teach calculus in schools, but I believe the most important formula is courage plus dreams equals success.', 67063, 0), (429612, 'Talking about dreams is like talking about movies, since the cinema uses the language of dreams; years can pass in a second, and you can hop from one place to another. It''s a language made of image. And in the real cinema, every object and every light means something, as in a dream.', 19735, 0), (429613, 'Today, among little girls especially, princesses and the romanticised ideal they represent - finding the man of your dreams - have a limited shelf life.', 68139, 0), (429614, 'I don''t use drugs, my dreams are frightening enough.', 20012, 0), (429615, 'No matter where you are from, no matter what your background is, no matter what your socioeconomic status is, every person can achieve his or her dreams.', 68140, 0), (429616, 'Dreams pass into the reality of action. From the actions stems the dream again and this interdependence produces the highest form of living. ', 23, 0), (429617, 'Dreams will get you nowhere, a good kick in the pants will take you a long way.', 1255, 0), (429618, 'We all dream; we do not understand our dreams, yet we act as if nothing strange goes on in our sleep minds, strange at least by comparison with the logical, purposeful doings of our minds when we are awake.', 190, 0), (429619, 'All men of action are dreamers.', 68141, 0), (429620, 'Like all dreamers, I mistook disenchantment for truth.', 592, 0), (429621, 'A man is not old until regrets take the place of dreams.', 26603, 0), (429622, 'Where all is but dream, reasoning and arguments are of no use, truth and knowledge nothing.', 2375, 0), (429623, 'Perhaps life is just that... a dream and a fear.', 1241, 0), (429624, 'To all, to each, a fair good-night, and pleasing dreams, and slumbers light.', 972, 0), (429625, 'Oh, I was never a businessman. I was a visionary, a dreamer.', 68142, 0), (429626, 'Dreams can become a reality when we possess a vision that is characterized by the willingness to 