INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429651, 'Dreams are the guiding words of the soul. Why should I henceforth not love my dreams and not make their riddling images into objects of my daily consideration?', 28934, 0), (429652, 'Dreams are illustrations from the book your soul is writing about you.', 9758, 0), (429653, 'The world is seldom what it seems; to man, who dimly sees, realities appear as dreams, and dreams realities.', 2087, 0), (429654, 'In our dreams we are always young.', 68149, 0), (429655, 'We''ve removed the ceiling above our dreams. There are no more impossible dreams.', 23411, 0), (429656, 'Intellectual despair results in neither weakness nor dreams, but in violence. It is only a matter of knowing how to give vent to one''s rage; whether one only wants to wander like madmen around prisons, or whether one wants to overturn them.', 2641, 0), (429657, 'In dreams the truth is learned that all good works are done in the absence of a caress.', 571, 0), (429658, 'The dialogue between client and architect is about as intimate as any conversation you can have, because when you''re talking about building a house, you''re talking about dreams.', 62542, 0), (429659, 'Dreams do come true, if we only wish hard enough, You can have anything in life if you will sacrifice everything else for it.', 64116, 0), (429660, 'When a child, my dreams rode on your wishes, I was your son, high on your horse, My mind a top whipped by the lashes Of your rhetoric, windy of course.', 37854, 0), (429661, 'We need affordable space travel to inspire our youth, to let them know that they can experience their dreams, can set significant goals and be in a position to lead all of us to future progress in exploration, discovery and fun. Thanks to the X Prize for the inspiration.', 68150, 0), (429662, 'Love is the most terrible, and also the most generous of the passions; it is the only one which includes in its dreams the happiness of someone else.', 26458, 0), (429663, 'I''d say it''s been my biggest problem all my life... it''s money. It takes a lot of money to make these dreams come true.', 65266, 0), (429664, 'Technology has a great advantage in that we are capable of creating dinosaurs and show them on the screen even though they are extinct 65 million years. All of a sudden, we have a fantastic tool that is as good as dreams are.', 2043, 0), (429665, 'Never let your dreams go away.', 68151, 0), (429666, 'My heroes, my dreams, and my future lay in Yankee Stadium. And they can''t take that away from me.', 66702, 0), (429667, 'The percentage you''re paying is too high priced While you''re living beyond all your means And the man in the suit has just bought a new car From the profit he''s made on your dreams.', 68152, 0), (429668, 'But we can hold our spirits and our bodies so pure and high, we may cherish such thoughts and such ideals, and dream such dreams of lofty purpose, that we can determine and know what manner of men we will be, whenever and wherever the hour strikes and calls to noble action.', 68153, 0), (429669, 'Field of Dreams is probably our generation''s It''s A Wonderful Life.', 36742, 0), (429670, 'Man is firmly convinced that he is awake in reality he is caught in a net of sleep and dreams which he has unconsciously woven himself. ', 68154, 0), (429671, 'Only in dreams, in poetry, in play do we sometimes arrive at what we were before we were this thing that, who knows, we are.', 149, 0), (429672, 'People who insist on telling their dreams are among the terrors of the breakfast table.', 17074, 0), (429673, 'The curse of the romantic is a greed for dreams, an intensity of expectation that, in the end, diminishes the reality.', 16394, 0), (429674, 'Our dreams are made of real things, like a shoebox full of photographs.', 707, 0), (429675, 'Seems like God don''t see fit to give the black man nothing but dreams - but He did give us children to make them dreams seem worthwhile.', 4386, 0), (429676, 'It takes someone with a vision of the possibilities to attain new levels of experience. Someone with the courage to live his dreams.', 1873, 0), (429677, 'Our life dreams the Utopia. Our death achieves the Ideal.', 98, 0), (429678, 'When you stop having dreams and ideals - well, you might as well stop altogether.', 15432, 0), (429679, 'You''ll be much more successful if you follow your dreams and follow your passions.', 67898, 0), (429680, 'Freedom and democracy are dreams you never give up.', 5358, 0), (429681, 'It has been my observation that parents kill more dreams than anybody.', 68155, 0), (429682, 'When I look back over my life it''s almost as if there was a plan laid out for me - from the little girl who was so passionate about animals who longed to go to Africa and whose family couldn''t afford to put her through college. Everyone laughed at my dreams. I was supposed to be a secretary in Bournemouth.', 2086, 0), (429683, 'Believe in and follow your dreams.', 68156, 0), (429684, 'I don''t understand people who dream in black and white. I just don''t get it. My dreams have always been vivid color.', 68157, 0), (429685, 'The motivation is in my heart to work toward my goals and my dreams.', 68158, 0), (429686, 'Like the phoenix, socialism is reborn from every pile of ashes left day in, day out, by burnt-out human dreams and charred hopes.', 33120, 0), (429687, 'Follow your intuition, listening to your dreams, your inner voice to guide you.', 68159, 0), (429688, 'As I and the rest of my Pittsburgh Steelers teammates prepared that week in late December 1974, we knew one thing: The road to the Super Bowl in the AFC went through Oakland. To achieve your dreams as a team, you had to slay the Oakland Raiders. They were the barometer of what it took to be a championship team.', 67203, 0), (429689, 'A visionary is someone who can see the future, or thinks he sees the future. In my case, I use it and it comes out right. That doesn''t come from daydreams or dreams, but it comes from knowing the market and knowing the world and knowing people really well and knowing where they''re going to be tomorrow.', 68160, 0), (429690, 'Thankfully, dreams can change. If we''d all stuck with our first dream, the world would be overrun with cowboys and princesses.', 1450, 0), (429691, 'Those of us who submitted or surrendered our ideas and dreams and identities to the ''leaders'' must take back our rights, our identities, our responsibilities.', 74, 0), (429692, 'I''m not more than a musician that enjoys what he does and a Colombian that dreams and fights for peace in his country.', 67930, 0), (429693, 'I have crazy claustrophobic dreams, weird elevator dreams where the elevator closes in and all of a sudden I am lying down - oh my God, it''s a casket. Just freaky stuff like that.', 22301, 0), (429694, 'I wanted to be a soccer player, and I became the best of the best, the number one, better than Maradona, better than Pele, and even better than Messi - but only at night, nighttime, during my dreams. When I wake up, I realized that I have wooden legs and that I''m doomed to be a writer.', 2140, 0), (429695, 'I believe people have to follow their dreams - I did.', 68161, 0), (429696, 'A strong mentor can help a young woman find and advance in the career of her dreams that otherwise may have seemed impossible.', 67406, 0), (429697, 'I wanted to be a musician, either a guitarist or a drummer. I guess my dreams were in the entertainment industry, and I landed somewhere along there.', 68162, 0), (429698, 'Sometimes just being on a beach with my loved ones is all the adventure I need. I am a happy camper and continue to be a citizen of the world. I have yet to discover other cultures, other peoples'' dreams and treasures. I will always be a traveler who is discovering beautiful Gaia.', 68163, 0), (429699, 'Every human heart cries and yearns for the same thing: a chance to fulfill his or her own dreams and desires. Even the poorest man has a dream.', 11162, 0), (429700, 'I had rock-star dreams from 8 or 9 almost nonstop. I thought it was going to be like being a god on earth: having as many women as you want whenever you want them, having super powers, being incredibly wealthy, never doing laundry.', 68164, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429701, 'I think it is often easier to make progress on mega-ambitious dreams. Since no one else is crazy enough to do it, you have little competition. In fact, there are so few people this crazy that I feel like I know them all by first name.', 19657, 0), (429702, '''Titanic'' made me want to tell stories... To have all these characters and costumes and have ambition and think big and have dreams... It came at a very troubled period of my life.', 68165, 0), (429703, 'The day you decide to pursue your dreams, don''t forget that this is a game you don''t enter to compete, but to win. And there will always be someone booing you in the stands, and everything you accomplish could be jeered and hissed at. This is a game between two that you have to win for the people who came to watch you be triumphant.', 19591, 0), (429704, 'We will bring back our jobs. We will bring back our borders. We will bring back our wealth. And we will bring back our dreams.', 64643, 0), (429705, 'We are in a world where globalization, which is an ideology, has forgotten and put aside the people, the people''s interests, aspirations, and dreams.', 67839, 0), (429706, 'To the degree we''re not living our dreams, our comfort zone has more control of us than we have over ourselves.', 30410, 0), (429707, 'A dream is a scripture, and many scriptures are nothing but dreams.', 736, 0), (429708, 'In the books I have written, I have created in my mind a universe. My kids say I have a village in my head and I live in that village, and it''s true. When I start writing a book, characters from previous books reappear. All my emotions, my mind, my heart, my dreams, everything becomes connected with a new book, and nothing else really matters.', 441, 0), (429709, 'The work of an advertising agency is warmly and immediately human. It deals with human needs, wants, dreams and hopes. Its ''product'' cannot be turned out on an assembly line.', 64007, 0), (429710, 'Yet it is in our idleness, in our dreams, that the submerged truth sometimes comes to the top.', 113, 0), (429711, 'Sports nurtures dreams of achieving self confidence and masculine striving for the skinny kid watching a boxer dance around the ring with sublime ease.', 46407, 0), (429712, 'But I have been interested in dreams, really since I was a kid. I have always been fascinated by the idea that your mind, when you are asleep, can create a world in a dream and you are perceiving it as though it really existed.', 11711, 0), (429713, 'My first book was called ''Buried Dreams,'' about a serial-killer, which was probably about ten years ahead of the serial-killer curve. It was a national bestseller, but it was three years of living in the sewer of this guy''s mind.', 26945, 0), (429714, 'My theory is that literature is essential to society in the way that dreams are essential to our lives. We can''t live without dreaming - as we can''t live without sleep. We are ''conscious'' beings for only a limited period of time, then we sink back into sleep - the ''unconscious.'' It is nourishing, in ways we can''t fully understand.', 852, 0), (429715, 'Even in the hardest circumstances, dreams can give you the courage to live, and I hope I can share that message with children in need.', 67489, 0), (429716, 'Women have to summon up courage to fulfill dormant dreams.', 753, 0), (429717, 'Private dreams are the most powerful. You have to dream of success to make it happen, and if you don''t believe in yourself, nobody else will. But that doesn''t mean you have to go around telling everyone about it.', 68166, 0), (429718, 'Pop culture shapes our ideas of what is normal and what our dreams can be and what our roles are. Politics, of course, decides how the power and the money in the country is distributed. Both are equally important, and each affects the other.', 1739, 0), (429719, 'The bipolar world of the Cold War is history. The new world order, however, is not the One World dreamed of by Wilsonian idealists. It is a Balkanizing world where race, tribe, culture and creed matter most, and democracy is seen not as an end in itself but as a means to an end - the accretion of power by one''s own kind to achieve one''s own dreams.', 54786, 0), (429720, 'In my perfect day, I wake up next to the woman of my dreams, and she''s crying tears of joy because she''s so excited about the life we have together. I''m preparing to compete in the 2016 Olympics with U.S.A. Team Handball, so I head to an intense training session with my coach to increase my physical strength and athleticism.', 66659, 0), (429721, 'When Paul Allen and I started Microsoft over 30 years ago, we had big dreams about software. We had dreams about the impact it could have.', 1133, 0), (429722, 'I just kind of wake up with a new idea and new dreams every day, and I follow that dream, as they say.', 1300, 0), (429723, 'My own dreams fortunately came true in this great state. I became Mr. Universe; I became a successful businessman. And even though some people say I still speak with a slight accent, I have reached the top of the acting profession.', 12194, 0), (429724, 'I came to the United States in the early ''80s and was welcomed with open arms and given the opportunity to pursue my dreams. God has been very kind to us. My family and I are fortunate enough to be successful and we feel a tremendous responsibility and obligation to give back to our great country.', 66796, 0), (429725, 'When we started Aftermath, we had something like 20 artists, and it was driving me crazy. I couldn''t sit down and focus on any of it. Plus, it was doubly hard because you ended up crushing these people''s dreams when you had to let them go.', 68167, 0), (429726, 'I have dreams that I will reach balance in my life, and, at forty-one, I have none.', 17895, 0), (429727, 'Most of us accept that although we may believe our dreams to be real events, upon waking, we can tell the difference between nocturnal hallucinations and reality.', 2777, 0), (429728, 'Progressives believe in making progress, which is why I''m proud to endorse Hillary Clinton, who I know will continue fighting to ensure our children and grandchildren can achieve their highest and best dreams.', 66634, 0), (429729, 'Tell me about yourself - your struggles, your dreams, your telephone number.', 64720, 0), (429730, 'Take what you can from your dreams, make them as real as anything.', 67345, 0), (429731, 'If you''re the type of person who has to fulfill your dreams, you''ve gotta be resourceful to make sure you can do it. I came out to California when I was 21, thinking my New York credentials would take me all the way. I came back home a year later all dejected and a failure.', 68102, 0), (429732, 'I motivate others by making sure that they understand to go after their dreams and don''t let anyone tell you you can''t. If you are motivated enough and put the work in that you can achieve anything in life that you set your mind to.', 67024, 0), (429733, 'I think there are a number of things that you can do to encourage your kids'' dreams, but I do believe in speaking by experience of having a lot of help along the way, stumbling in the past. We''ve all stumbled, and we certainly all deserve to get up and walk again.', 11331, 0), (429734, 'If you can''t read, it''s going to be hard to realize dreams.', 5998, 0), (429735, 'Lonesome. Lonesome. I know what it means. Here all by my lonesome, dreaming empty dreams. Weary. Weary at the close of day, wondering if tomorrow brings me joy or sorrow.', 68168, 0), (429736, 'Those who have compared our life to a dream were right... we were sleeping wake, and waking sleep.', 663, 0), (429737, 'I have a notebook that is filled to the brim with my dreams and ideas and goals and aspirations.', 68169, 0), (429738, 'That''s what noir feels like to me. It feels like some kind of recurring dream, with very strong archetypes operating. You know, the guilty girl being pursued, falling, all kinds of stuff that we see in our dreams all the time.', 68170, 0), (429739, 'Dreams sometimes foretell the future.', 68171, 0), (429740, 'Dream no small dreams for they have no power to move the hearts of men.', 282, 0), (429741, 'I stayed true to my dreams and, eventually, they came true.', 44935, 0), (429742, 'My new life goes beyond my dreams because my dream was Formula One and I achieved it. I''m a driver, I feel like a driver. I have won this race because I am alive.', 68172, 0), (429743, 'I do not know whether I was then a man dreaming I was a butterfly, or whether I am now a butterfly dreaming I am a man.', 2480, 0), (429744, 'Dream lofty dreams, and as you dream, so you shall become. Your vision is the promise of what you shall one day be; your ideal is the prophecy of what you shall at last unveil.', 2970, 0), (429745, 'I have been interested in dreams, really since I was a kid. I have always been fascinated by the idea that your mind, when you are asleep, can create a world in a dream and you are perceiving it as though it really existed.', 11711, 0), (429746, 'A lot of people do not muster the courage to live their dreams because they are afraid to die.', 1873, 0), (429747, 'I am accustomed to sleep and in my dreams to imagine the same things that lunatics imagine when awake.', 2272, 0), (429748, 'To be a footballer was just a dream, and I don''t believe in dreams. I only deal in what is real. To be honest, I''ve never thought about what I could get out of football or where it would take me. I just wanted to play. I''m the same now.', 68173, 0), (429749, 'Like dreams, statistics are a form of wish fulfillment.', 8077, 0), (429750, 'I want that longevity in the career, so if you don''t know how to get it, you trying to chase that high, you trying to continue to chase your dreams and conquer things you never thought you could get. And you just want to get there too soon, so you taking the wrong moves to try and compensate what''s not happening.', 68174, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429751, 'Capitalism is always evaluated against dreams. Utopia is a dream. It doesn''t exist.', 17531, 0), (429752, 'The real hero is always a hero by mistake he dreams of being an honest coward like everybody else. ', 736, 0), (429753, 'Living in dreams of yesterday, we find ourselves still dreaming of impossible future conquests.', 37323, 0), (429754, 'But I, being poor, have only my dreams; I have spread my dreams under your feet; Tread softly because you tread on my dreams.', 62867, 0), (429755, 'Reality seems valueless by comparison with the dreams of fevered imaginations reality is therefore abandoned. ', 15804, 0), (429756, 'Though we may have desires or bold goals, for whatever reason, most of us don''t think we can achieve something beyond what we''re qualified to achieve. Why, I ask, do we let reality interfere with our dreams?', 19485, 0), (429757, 'Glamour is an imaginative process that creates a specific emotional response: a sharp mixture of projection, longing, admiration, and aspiration. It evokes an audience''s hopes and dreams and makes them seem attainable, all the while maintaining enough distance to sustain the fantasy.', 68175, 0), (429758, 'You don''t know when you are immersed in a book what the reaction to it will be, but I feel great about ''The Lake of Dreams.''', 8033, 0), (429759, 'I always make my dreams into goals.', 68176, 0), (429760, 'Anyone who has spent any time in space will love it for the rest of their lives. I achieved my childhood dream of the sky.', 68177, 0), (429761, 'Dream small dreams. If you make them too big, you get overwhelmed and you don''t do anything. If you make small goals and accomplish them, it gives you the confidence to go on to higher goals.', 68178, 0), (429762, 'Not all lucid dreams are useful but they all have a sense of wonder about them. If you must sleep through a third of your life, why should you sleep through your dreams, too?', 44406, 0), (429763, 'Life being what it is, one dreams of revenge.', 1948, 0), (429764, 'Dreams are the touchstones of our character.', 1049, 0), (429765, 'I''ll tell you this: You have to remember to chase and catch your dreams, because if you don''t, your imagination will live in empty spaces, and that''s nowhere land.', 68179, 0), (429766, 'I would love to spend all my time writing to you; I''d love to share with you all that goes through my mind, all that weighs on my heart, all that gives air to my soul; phantoms of art, dreams that would be so beautiful if they could come true.', 23247, 0), (429767, 'You know, the man of my dreams might walk round the corner tomorrow. I''m older and wiser and I think I''d make a great girlfriend. I live in the realm of romantic possibility.', 2108, 0), (429768, 'When I began to choreograph and find my way pulling other artists'' dreams out and changing music in a visual way, there was still a part of me that had something more to say. There was still a desire to rock a stage and ultimately perform the eight count of my dream, but there was a lot of insecurity there.', 68180, 0), (429769, 'I''ve got big, big dreams for the future.', 68181, 0), (429770, 'When I was a kid, I have two dreams. I want to be a baseball player. Hometown, Hiroshima, has a Japanese baseball franchise team called Hiroshima Carps. You know, and then I want to be a sushi chef. I want to make own restaurant - sushi restaurant.', 68182, 0), (429771, 'I have had a dream indicating rather clearly that I am on the way to being hetero, though I don''t accept it with much enthusiasm either awake or in the dreams.', 1918, 0), (429772, 'I am against nature. I don''t dig nature at all. I think nature is very unnatural. I think the truly natural things are dreams, which nature can''t touch with decay.', 289, 0), (429773, 'We never want to go into a tour and play 15 songs and say ''Enjoy.'' We have messages: Number 1, follow your dreams. If I can do it, you can do it. Number 2, give your life to something. We say, ''Volunteer and add seven years to your life.'' You can have your own personal ministry. The message we have is ''What do you stand for?''', 68113, 0), (429774, 'I dream that someday the step between my mind and my finger will no longer be needed. And that simply by blinking my eyes, I shall make pictures. Then, I think, I shall really have become a photographer.', 46569, 0), (429775, 'Sometimes I wake at night in the White House and rub my eyes and wonder if it is not all a dream.', 18162, 0), (429776, 'I''ve always said that one night, I''m going to find myself in some field somewhere, I''m standing on grass, and it''s raining, and I''m with the person I love, and I know I''m at the very point I''ve been dreaming of getting to.', 292, 0), (429777, 'You know, Willie Wonka said it best: we are the makers of dreams, the dreamers of dreams.', 68183, 0), (429778, 'I believe history will come to view 9/11 as an event on par with November 22, 1963, the date on which John F. Kennedy was murdered, cutting short a presidency that was growing ever more promising. Dreams died that day in Dallas; it is easy to imagine the 1960s turning out rather differently had President Kennedy lived.', 19516, 0), (429779, 'Technically a memoir, ''The Woman Warrior'' becomes almost magical through its inclusion of folk tales, dreams, and revisions.', 3593, 0), (429780, 'You have to be vigorous. That''s the only way you are going to get it because everybody has dreams and everybody has goals, but the only people who achieve them are the ones that go after it and don''t take no for an answer.', 67879, 0), (429781, 'If you want to achieve your dreams, you must follow them, and the best way to follow them is not to think about wanting to be very rich, but to think about doing something that you really want to do.', 566, 0), (429782, 'No matter how carefully you plan your goals they will never be more than pipe dreams unless you pursue them with gusto.', 3433, 0), (429783, 'I can never decide whether my dreams are the result of my thoughts, or my thoughts the result of my dreams.', 178, 0), (429784, 'I''m a really hectic dreamer; I never wake up not out of a dream, and there''s loads going on, lots of action, big blockbuster dreams, they''re all major enterprises.', 17589, 0), (429785, 'In the Seventies, we still had dreams and hopes of Utopia, but by the end of the decade, the world had shifted to the right.', 17501, 0), (429786, 'American dreams are strongest in the hearts of those who have seen America only in their dreams.', 711, 0), (429787, 'It is one of the blessings of this world that few people see visions and dream dreams.', 751, 0), (429788, 'When you have a dream that you can''t let go of, trust your instincts and pursue it. But remember: Real dreams take work, They take patience, and sometimes they require you to dig down very deep. Be sure you''re willing to do that.', 25461, 0), (429789, 'I was not looking for my dreams to interpret my life, but rather for my life to interpret my dreams.', 4673, 0), (429790, 'There has been enough suffering in our country, there has been enough of children whose dreams die before they have a chance to grow and there has been enough of our elders who, having served their nation, are forced into indignity in their old age.', 68184, 0), (429791, 'My dreams were at once more fantastic and agreeable than my writings.', 68126, 0), (429792, 'There are women succeeding beyond their wildest dreams because of their sobriety.', 2326, 0), (429793, 'If you always think about your dreams or goals, work steadfastly towards them and continue to challenge yourself, you will definitely be able to realise those dreams or goals.', 68185, 0), (429794, 'Dream in a pragmatic way.', 1032, 0), (429795, 'A daydream is an evasion.', 123, 0), (429796, 'You can plant a dream.', 6514, 0), (429797, 'All art is exorcism. I paint dreams and visions too; the dreams and visions of my time. Painting is the effort to produce order; order in yourself. There is much chaos in me, much chaos in our time.', 68186, 0), (429798, 'Humanity needs dreams to be able to survive the miseries of daily existence, even if only for an instant.', 68187, 0), (429799, 'Horror, for me, has to involve some sort of fantasy. Horror is something that is in your dreams or your nightmares.', 68188, 0), (429800, 'In my dreams I hear again the crash of guns, the rattle of musketry, the strange, mournful mutter of the battlefield.', 2273, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429801, 'Man, alone, has the power to transform his thoughts into physical reality; man, alone, can dream and make his dreams come true.', 1187, 0), (429802, 'Obviously one must hold oneself responsible for the evil impulses of one''s dreams. In what other way can one deal with them? Unless the content of the dream rightly understood is inspired by alien spirits, it is part of my own being.', 555, 0), (429803, 'After all those days in the cotton fields, the dreams came true on a gold record on a piece of wood. It''s in my den where I can look at it every day. I wear it out lookin'' at it.', 68189, 0), (429804, 'It''s not only imagination, it''s the distortion of the vision. You suddenly think, This person is idealistic, this person is strong, this person has dreams, when you know better most of the time. You put what you want to see on people.', 68190, 0), (429805, 'Do It Under the Influence Yourself! That''s what we''re shooting for! Get drunk and make your dreams come true.', 12128, 0), (429806, 'I''ve been interested in dreams since I as a kid and I''ve wanted to do a film about them for a long time.', 11711, 0), (429807, 'You have to work hard for what you want to achieve and you have to set goals and dreams and really go for them.', 68191, 0), (429808, 'Barack Obama knows that to create an economy built to last, we need to focus on middle-class families. Families who stay up on Sunday nights pacing the floor, like my dad did, while their children, tucked in bed, dream big dreams. Families who aren''t sure what Monday morning will bring, but who believe our nation''s best days are still ahead.', 67564, 0), (429809, 'When we see the face of a child, we think of the future. We think of their dreams about what they might become, and what they might accomplish.', 2109, 0), (429810, 'Happiness is making your dreams come true.', 68192, 0), (429811, 'The working class of England take their deracination completely for granted. Disenchantment is the happy code that informs every byway of the underclass: service jobs, celebrity dreams, Lotto wins, leisured poverty on pre-crunch credit cards, it''s all there, part of the story of an English people whose grandparents never had it so good.', 68193, 0), (429812, 'I dream a lot, in colour and in sound and scent. Quite a few of my stories have come from dreams.', 5844, 0), (429813, 'My mother always gives the best advice. When I left Puerto Rico to pursue my dreams, she always supported me and said to me, ''I''m never going to cut your wings, so don''t let anyone else do that to you.'' That has been my philosophy through life. I want to share that valuable lesson with my little girl someday.', 68194, 0), (429814, 'I would like to instill in people just to work hard. As long as they keep at it, their dreams will happen.', 68195, 0), (429815, 'I used to work at a movie theater and sold hams at Honey Baked Ham during the holidays. I sold a ton of hams, and they offered me a regular job there, which I turned down. I feel like anything you do, just do it 100% because then that work ethic will bleed through when it''s time to work on your dreams.', 68122, 0), (429816, 'What is happiness other than a negotiation between reality and your dreams? It''s understanding that you give up something for something else. I feel like that''s been how I''ve been trying to be happy, although in my DNA there''s more of a depressed person.', 67788, 0), (429817, 'You can go slow. Allow your dreams and goals to change, but live an intentional life.', 68196, 0), (429818, 'Our dreams are a second life. I have never been able to penetrate without a shudder those ivory or horned gates which separate us from the invisible world.', 16473, 0), (429819, 'It isn''t a calamity to die with dreams unfulfilled, but it is a calamity not to dream.', 4711, 0), (429820, 'Old folks have dreams and ambitions too, like everybody else. Don''t sit on a couch someplace.', 14739, 0), (429821, 'To every people the land is given on condition. Perceived or not, there is a Covenant, beyond the constitution, beyond sovereign guarantee, beyond the nation''s sweetest dreams of itself.', 571, 0), (429822, 'This is the city of dreamers and time and again it''s the place where the greatest dream of all, the American dream, has been tested and has triumphed.', 67699, 0), (429823, 'Take pleasure in your dreams relish your principles and drape your purest feelings on the heart of a precious lover. ', 32709, 0), (429824, 'Thanking you once more, I want to wish you the best of luck for your future life and to conclude by saying to you: Dream your dreams and may they come true!', 41952, 0), (429825, 'We need to be aware of what we are capable of first and realize that if you place your dreams really really high, you do have the potential to get to that level.', 67843, 0), (429826, 'Inspiration comes from so many sources. Music, other fiction, the non-fiction I read, TV shows, films, news reports, people I know, stories I hear, misheard words or lyrics, dreams... Motivation? The memory of the rush I get from a really good writing session - even on a bad day, I know I''ll find that again if I keep going.', 905, 0), (429827, 'If you''re following your dreams, you''re doing something you love and that you believe in yourself for.', 68197, 0), (429828, 'To be a human being is to be in a state of tension between your appetites and your dreams, and the social realities around you and your obligations to your fellow man.', 135, 0), (429829, 'There''s a lot of people that have great ideas and dreams and whatnot, but unless you''re willing to work really, really hard, and work for what you want, it''s never going to happen.', 68198, 0), (429830, 'If you ask me, there''s nothing more incredible than a woman who''s in charge of her own destiny - and working daily to make her dreams a reality.', 26172, 0), (429831, 'My story, I feel like it''s amazing, because it shows people no matter where you come from, no matter what your lifestyle is, your dreams could still come true if you believe in yourself and push hard to do what you want to do.', 39677, 0), (429832, 'God''s gifts put man''s best dreams to shame.', 157, 0), (429833, 'The dreamer can know no truth, not even about his dream, except by awaking out of it.', 2683, 0), (429834, 'No one should negotiate their dreams. Dreams must be free to fly high. No government, no legislature, has a right to limit your dreams. You should never agree to surrender your dreams.', 23411, 0), (429835, 'When you cease to dream you cease to live.', 5930, 0), (429836, 'Only the dreamer shall understand realities, though in truth his dreaming must be not out of proportion to his waking.', 2792, 0), (429837, 'You gotta have a dream. If you don''t have a dream, how you gonna make a dream come true?', 43349, 0), (429838, 'I challenge you to be dreamers I challenge you to be doers and let us make the greatest place in the world even better. ', 68199, 0), (429839, 'Dreams must be heeded and accepted. For a great many of them come true.', 2652, 0), (429840, 'Dreaming or awake, we perceive only events that have meaning to us.', 16477, 0), (429841, 'I''ve said it before, but it''s absolutely true: My mother gave me my drive, but my father gave me my dreams. Thanks to him, I could see a future.', 68200, 0), (429842, 'I was so lucky to have parents who supported me, 100%, with whatever I was doing, both financially and emotionally. Having that they made my life so much easier. Instead of becoming a bartender and trying to survive while trying to pursue your dreams, I didn''t have to worry about that aspect. I could just pursue my dreams.', 68201, 0), (429843, 'My parent''s divorce and hard times at school, all those things combined to mold me, to make me grow up quicker. And it gave me the drive to pursue my dreams that I wouldn''t necessarily have had otherwise.', 11155, 0), (429844, 'People are never more insecure than when they become obsessed with their fears at the expense of their dreams.', 7782, 0), (429845, 'Hollywood has always been a cage... a cage to catch our dreams.', 45115, 0), (429846, 'Learn from your dreams what you lack.', 219, 0), (429847, 'Dreams get you into the future and add excitement to the present.', 68202, 0), (429848, 'O reason, reason, abstract phantom of the waking state, I had already expelled you from my dreams, now I have reached a point where those dreams are about to become fused with apparent realities: now there is only room here for myself.', 16839, 0), (429849, 'It''s not my job to dream your dreams. It''s my job to make your dreams become a reality.', 67784, 0), (429850, 'A successful life is one that is lived through understanding and pursuing one''s own path, not chasing after the dreams of others.', 57610, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429851, 'Dreaming in public is an important part of our job description, as science writers, but there are bad dreams as well as good dreams. We''re dreamers, you see, but we''re also realists, of a sort.', 9661, 0), (429852, 'They were using the dolls to project their dreams of their own futures as adult women.', 66729, 0), (429853, 'I came at age in the ''60s, and initially my hopes and dreams were invested in politics and the movements of the time - the anti-war movement, the civil rights movement. I worked on Bobby Kennedy''s campaign for president as a teenager in California and the night he was killed.', 19631, 0), (429854, 'We must not let our passions destroy our dreams.', 327, 0), (429855, 'I''ve succeeded beyond my wildest dreams - financially and the amount of fun I have in my life.', 68203, 0), (429856, 'Dreams are not without meaning wherever thay may come from-from fantasy, from the elements, or from other inspiration.', 2652, 0), (429857, 'Women are not in love with me but with the picture of me on the screen. I am merely the canvas on which women paint their dreams.', 68204, 0), (429858, 'Books that distribute things... with as daring a freedom as we use in dreams, put us on our feet again.', 2664, 0), (429859, 'It is an everlasting desire to make my dreams come true. And it''s getting to the point now where it''s like, come on I want my dreams to come true so that I can get on with the rest of my life. Sometimes I think about the rest of my life when I''m done.', 54969, 0), (429860, 'My mother taught me that we all have the power to achieve our dreams. What I lacked was the courage.', 68205, 0), (429861, 'Death is the mother of Beauty; hence from her, alone, shall come fulfillment to our dreams and our desires.', 2547, 0), (429862, 'I''m aware of the mystery around us, so I write about coincidences, premonitions, emotions, dreams, the power of nature, magic.', 441, 0), (429863, 'With unemployment still abysmally high, the Obama economy is crushing Hispanics'' dreams for their children to live a better life.', 66707, 0), (429864, 'America allows us to be able to dream, then gives us the ability to achieve those dreams.', 68206, 0), (429865, 'My dreams are of water. And my nightmares.', 68207, 0), (429866, 'I say to my colleagues never confine your best work, your hopes, your dreams, the aspiration of the American people to what will be signed by George W. Bush because that is too limiting a factor.', 50900, 0), (429867, 'You''ve got to have a dream... if you don''t have any big dreams, nothing happens.', 67757, 0), (429868, 'All my dreams are coming true all across the board for some reason.', 68208, 0), (429869, 'The ideal of all Kosovo is membership in the E.U. and a permanent friendship with the United States. I believe and I am convinced our dreams will come true.', 68209, 0), (429870, 'You don''t ever want to go out there and not be the best. You want to be the best cop that you can. Be the best writer you can be. Everybody has their goals. Everybody has their dreams.', 67886, 0), (429871, 'There is no better gift a society can give children than the opportunity to grow up safe and free - the chance to pursue whatever dreams they may have.', 68210, 0), (429872, '''Shake It Up'' definitely teaches kids about the importance of reaching for your dreams and setting high goals. It also teaches great lessons about friendship and family.', 68211, 0), (429873, 'I don''t think the dreams die - I think that people give up. I think it gets too hard.', 1776, 0), (429874, 'Learning to read and write changes lives; it means jobs, money, health, and dreams fulfilled.', 67571, 0), (429875, 'For me, the sketching of dresses was about fantasy and dreams. In my little room at home, I felt that I was somewhere else. In Paris, for instance.', 68212, 0), (429876, 'It''s good to have plans and dreams, but don''t be surprised if God brings you somewhere else.', 68213, 0), (429877, 'People think it''s funny that I enjoy dreaming so much. I just use it as a form of entertainment. It''s very private. I don''t see my dreams as separate. I mean, half the time I''m wandering around dreaming anyway.', 68214, 0), (429878, 'We will be returning to historical levels of inequality. We''ll view post-war America as a kind of strange interlude not to be repeated. It won''t be the dreams that we all had that virtually all incomes go up in lockstep at three percent a year. It hurts to give that up.', 24595, 0), (429879, 'We''re not teaching our students the importance of relationships with other people: how you work with them, what the relational pathology consists of, how you examine your own conscience, how you examine the inner world, how you examine your dreams.', 1196, 0), (429880, 'There is no substitute under the heavens for productive labor. It is the process by which dreams become realities. It is the process by which idle visions become dynamic achievements.', 197, 0), (429881, 'Even in the most peaceful communities, an appetite for violence shows up in dreams, fantasies, sports, play, literature, movies and television. And, so long as we don''t transform into angels, violence and the threat of violence - as in punishment and deterrence - is needed to rein in our worst instincts.', 28944, 0), (429882, 'No one respects the First Amendment more than I do. People have a right to express their concerns and their hopes and dreams to their government.', 68215, 0), (429883, 'I plan to see St. Louis as a global competitor. As an international trade hub, as an incubator of new companies, as a place of culture and the arts, as a magnet for immigrants, for entrepreneurs, for animal lovers, and for gays, as a city of parks and trails, and as the sort of place that figures in young people''s dreams.', 68216, 0), (429884, 'I lived for two years in Odawara, a castle town an hour outside of Tokyo, near the sea. It''s a beautiful place, and I drew on my experiences there when writing ''The Lake of Dreams.''', 8033, 0), (429885, 'Some guys have trouble sleeping the night before an important round. I never have. Invariably, I sleep longer and better, and have more dreams, when I''m in contention and feeling pressure.', 68217, 0), (429886, 'You can''t predict it all. People will tell you to plan things out as best you can. They will tell you to focus. They will tell you to follow your dreams. They will all be right.', 23090, 0), (429887, 'In my dreams, I have Keira Knightley''s eyebrows.', 12145, 0), (429888, 'Reagan never cottoned to dictators. He was pure in this notion in a true belief that democracy was the best solution in the world because it spoke to people''s hopes and dreams and aspirations, freedom of religion, freedom of speech, freedom of speech.', 19715, 0), (429889, 'I''ve always been interested in photographing traditions and customs - especially in America. The prom is an American tradition, a rite of passage that has always been one of the most important rituals of American youth. It is a day in our lives that we never forget - a day full of hopes and dreams for our future.', 68218, 0), (429890, 'I think what people need to realize is that, with trans people, we''re like everybody else. No group of people are all the same. All women are not the same, all men are not the same, all children are not the same. It''s the same thing with trans people - we''re all so different, we have different goals, different dreams, and different aspirations.', 68219, 0), (429891, 'For anyone aspiring to be anything, I would like them to realise dreams require work. So work big time.', 68220, 0), (429892, 'We are certainly not to relinquish the evidence of experiments for the sake of dreams and vain fictions of our own devising; nor are we to recede from the analogy of Nature, which is wont to be simple and always consonant to itself.', 2482, 0), (429893, 'I know God loves me. I tell people all the time I''m one of his favorite childs. I had to believe in something bigger than me - bigger than man. I had to believe that God would send somebody across my path to keep my dreams alive.', 68221, 0), (429894, 'I am, you know, really fighting for myself and my life. And I think the message that I could give to anybody is that it''s never too late to start your life again and dream new dreams.', 68222, 0), (429895, 'When you''re a Republican Latino, you''re traveling uphill on a lonely road. Still, it''s the road I prefer. It has led me to opportunity far beyond my dreams. I''ve worked on eight Republican presidential races, as well as for some of the world''s largest corporations, all because the doors of opportunity, not the doors of welfare, were open to me.', 68223, 0), (429896, 'As aspiring athletes, you should never give up on your dreams. Just believe in yourself, and everything will be possible.', 68224, 0), (429897, 'Integrity is critical to our lives - and to our dreams of achievement. We must remember that without integrity, nothing else matters and that with integrity, nothing else matters.', 68225, 0), (429898, 'Mother believed that I should have an enormous amount of sleep, and so I was never really tired when I went to bed. This was the best time of day, when I could lie in the vague twilight, drifting off to sleep, making up dreams inside my head the way they should go.', 140, 0), (429899, 'You can''t just constantly judge a situation or a person because of what you''re used to or how they look. They might turn out to be this sweet man who asks you what your dreams are. You know?', 68226, 0), (429900, 'When I came to America, I dreamed bigger dreams.', 20529, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (429901, 'Ours is the job of interpreting the Constitution. And that document isn''t some inkblot on which litigants may project their hopes and dreams.', 66620, 0), (429902, 'My greatest mistake is that my dreams were too small.', 4770, 0), (429903, 'I''ve shown that if you dream and are willing to work hard, you can achieve your dreams.', 67746, 0), (429904, 'If you live close to an International Rescue Committee office in the United States, find out how you can assist a refugee family as they transition to American life. Invite a newly arrived family to your home for a welcoming meal. Listen to their hopes and dreams, and share your own.', 34499, 0), (429905, 'In Hollywood, normally things don''t work out, and dreams are crushed.', 68227, 0), (429906, 'I''m fulfilling my dreams that I had as a kid every single day. That''s why I''m trying to enjoy it so much.', 68228, 0), (429907, 'If I''m lucky, in my wildest dreams I can make a picture every three years.', 68229, 0), (429908, 'In a democracy, if you don''t get the votes, nothing else is possible, no matter how wonderful your dreams.', 67891, 0), (429909, 'I have lived with my husband more than I have with my parents... I live beside him, and know his worries, his hopes, and his dreams for his nation. We believe that things happen by design, not in an arbitrary way. And we believe it is our duty to make things happen.', 68230, 0), (429910, 'To wear dreams on one''s feet is to begin to give a reality to one''s dreams.', 68231, 0), (429911, 'Films are dreams. Many, many critics say to me that my films are not good because they are too unbelievable, but this is my style. I tell stories like they are dreams. This is my imagination. For me, it would be impossible to do a film that is so precise, that resembles real life.', 68232, 0), (429912, 'Hold on to your dream. Don''t let past failures or dire economic forecasts make you a pessimist. Keep your youthful dreams alive and create your own opportunities.', 5479, 0), (429913, 'For all life is a dream, and dreams themselves are only dreams.', 84, 0), (429914, 'I don''t like dreams or reality. I like when dreams become reality because that is my life.', 68233, 0), (429915, 'There''s a line I have that our family was designed more for public than for private. But there are definitely some things that are only mine. I am someone who dreams at night, and you don''t know what I''m dreaming.', 1288, 0), (429916, 'When you''re a kid, you have these big ideas and these big dreams to make a change, or maybe you feel like you can''t make a difference.', 49386, 0), (429917, 'I never expected anyone to take care of me, but in my wildest dreams and juvenile yearnings, I wanted the house with the picket fence from June Allyson movies. I knew that was yearning like one yearns to fly.', 74, 0), (429918, 'When your dreams include service to others - accomplishing something that contributes to others - it also accelerates the accomplishment of that goal. People want to be part of something that contributes and makes a difference.', 1834, 0), (429919, 'I like to surround myself with people that have dreams and that fight for them every day.', 68234, 0), (429920, 'A lot of dreams can turn to nightmares... if you don''t really work them.', 1300, 0), (429921, 'By nature, I''m a very positive person, and because I''m happy in myself, and in my life, and I''ve got a great husband, and beautiful children, and I have a job that I love that calls for a certain amount of emotional expression, I get to realise a lot of my dreams and aspirations.', 22748, 0), (429922, 'What I would say to young entrepreneurs is there''s so many moments in your life where you have these dreams, and people are trying to protect you, and they say, perhaps, friends, family, parents sometimes, they don''t agree with it, they think, ''This is just too high of a hurdle.'' And I don''t agree with that.', 19506, 0), (429923, 'You really can have your dreams and at the same time have a family. But it has to be a really deliberate practice.', 67788, 0), (429924, 'Before dance came into my life, I don''t really remember having any major goals or dreams of wanting to be anything.', 50400, 0), (429925, 'I do not have bad days. I don''t wake up in the morning and think that I''m going to get AIDS. I don''t dream bad dreams about it. If I did, I''d be giving in to the negativity.', 67024, 0), (429926, 'For me, having walked through Times Square so many times as a broke and starving artist, as a TV star, and now having other hopes and dreams, it just represents possibility and the moment of full circle.', 68235, 0), (429927, 'I really want to live in New York. That''s the city of my dreams.', 68236, 0), (429928, 'I like to keep the median age in my lab low because they will indulge me in my dreams. They don''t yet think things are impossible.', 68237, 0), (429929, 'When younger writers and poets, musicians and painters are weakened by a stemming of funds, they come to me saddened, not as full of dreams and excitement and ideas. I am then weakened and diminished, and made less rich.', 74, 0), (429930, 'A man is a god in ruins. When men are innocent, life shall be longer, and shall pass into the immortal, as gently as we awake from dreams.', 760, 0), (429931, 'I still have dreams about CBGB''s. I still miss the place.', 68, 0), (429932, 'My experience of malaria was just taking anti-malarials, which give you strange dreams, because I don''t want to get malaria.', 1133, 0), (429933, 'You know, my dad served in the President''s Cabinet after his time as a governor. He told me he enjoyed being governor a lot more. Now, I understand why. If I do my job well, I can make a difference in people''s lives and I can help our children realize their dreams.', 52321, 0), (429934, 'I would honestly say that with all the awards and all the other things that I''ve done in my life, Dollywood is one of the greatest dreams that I''ve ever had come true - I am so proud of that I can''t even begin to tell you, Dollywood is real special to me.', 1300, 0), (429935, 'Everybody past a certain age, regardless of how they look on the outside, pretty much constantly dreams of being able to escape from their lives.', 1002, 0), (429936, 'When I was 20, the idea of having a play on anywhere was just beyond my dreams.', 408, 0), (429937, 'What is the conservative movement? It''s pretty straightforward. We believe that the way prosperity is created is when people have the freedom and the opportunity to pursue their dreams.', 66707, 0), (429938, 'Mitt Romney will stop the attacks on job creators, encourage entrepreneurs to chase their dreams, and bring good jobs and a better future to all Americans.', 66707, 0), (429939, 'We''re special because dreams that are impossible anywhere else, come true here. That''s not just my story. That''s your story. That''s our story.', 66707, 0), (429940, 'Here in America, those who once had no hope will give their kids the chance at a life they always wanted for themselves. Here in America, generations of unfulfilled dreams will finally come to pass.', 66707, 0), (429941, 'They made it to the middle class, my dad working as a bartender and my mother as a cashier and a maid. I didn''t inherit any money from them. But I inherited something far better - the real opportunity to accomplish my dreams.', 66707, 0), (429942, 'To this day, some of my closest friends say, ''Gaga, you know, everything''s great. You''re a singer; your dreams have come true.'' But, still, when certain things are said to you over and over again as you''re growing up, it stays with you and you wonder if they''re true.', 47, 0), (429943, 'I am a walking piece of art every day, with my dreams and my ambitions forward at all times in an effort to inspire my fans to lead their life in that way.', 47, 0), (429944, 'There are a lot of things that are personally uncomfortable to show, especially me without makeup and completely bloated or crying. But I''ve realized that it''s time for me to show my audience that you don''t have to be perfect to achieve your dreams. Because nobody relates to being perfect.', 746, 0), (429945, 'There''s always going to be dreams and goals I have, but I never really tell people what they are.', 1725, 0), (429946, '''Modelland'' has always been a part of my mind and my heart. I''m excited that you''ll be able to read about this magical world that''s been living in my dreams for so many years.', 1725, 0), (429947, 'I''ve made mistakes before of doing different projects just based on my dreams, my hopes, my thing, and not really thinking about my customers.', 1725, 0), (429948, 'Going back to the moon is not visionary in restoring space leadership for America. Like its Apollo predecessor, it will prove to be a dead end littered with broken spacecraft, broken dreams and broken policies.', 25693, 0), (429949, 'Dreams come true; without that possibility, nature would not incite us to have them.', 135, 0), (429950, 'Economics is not a science; it is a quasi-religion: part superstition, part mystique, part sentimentality. Bankers dream like other men, the only difference being that when their dreams turn to nightmares, we all lose sleep. There can be no trusting the muttering of any prelate when it comes to money.', 4223, 0);
